Commentary: Not a very good ball to start off and India are underway. Philander bowls this one on the pads. Agarwal flicks this one towards square leg and takes a single to get off the mark.
Length ball outside off, Rohit Sharma shoulders arms to it.

Good length ball outside off, Rohit pushes at it. The ball finds the edge of the bat and goes towards the man at gully. He misfields and that allows the batters to take the run. Rohit Sharma is off the mark.
Length ball outside off, nipping away. Agarwal looks to fend at it initially but pulls his bat away at the last moment. Close call!
On the pads, Agarwal flicks this one towards the mid-wicket region.
Good ball to end the over by Philander. This one pitches on a length, nips away from the batter. Agarwal looks to play at it but does so inside the line and is beaten.
Sharma defends this off the front foot by presenting the full face of the bat.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Sharma.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards point by Sharma.

Runs! On the pads this time, Sharma flicks this one towards mid-wicket. The batters take off as the fielder from mid on hares after the ball to stop it. He does so inside the fence and the batters take three.
Length ball outside off, Mayank shoulders arms to let that one through.
Way wide outside off, swinging even further away. Agarwal makes a comfortable leave.

Beautiful ball to start off the over! Good length ball just outside off, Sharma looks to defend it by getting on the front foot but he misses the ball due to the away movement on it. Beaten all ends up!
Philander bowls this one too wide. Sharma does not do anything to make any contact on this one.
On the pads of Sharma, he flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a couple.
Good length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.
Good length ball again, nipping back in to Sharma. He plays a forward defense but he gets an inside edge on it. The ball thuds into his pads.
Sharma shuffles across, covers his stumps and makes the leave.
Length ball outside off by Rabada, Agarwal makes the leave.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards point off the back foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball wide outside off, Agarwal looks to fend at it. He gets a thick outside edge on it as the ball flies towards the gap between gully and third slip. The fielder at gully tries to catch it with a dive to his left but the ball races away to the third man fence. Agarwal riding his luck!
No ball! Rabada oversteps! Length ball on middle and off, Agarwal defends this one off the back foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fullish this time, Agarwal pushes this one straight down the ground but the bowler stops it.
Outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Length ball outside off by Philander, Sharma leaves it alone.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
On the pads, Sharma flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a single.

NOT OUT! That looked plumb at first but the umpire's call has saved Agarwal here! Philander bowls a good length ball just outside off, jagging back in. Agarwal looks to defend it but misses. The South African players go up in appeal, they are convinced that they have got their man but the umpire is unmoved. South Africa take the review almost immediately. Ultra Edge confirms no bat involved. Ball Tracker comes in, shows umpire's call on impact and wickets as well as this one is clipping the top of off. Mayank survives, barely!
Wide outside off stump, Agarwal leaves it alone.
Another length ball outside off, left alone by the batter.
Outside off, extra bounce, fended towards point.
Length ball on middle and off, Sharma defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends it out.
Landed outside off, Rohit feels for it but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma tries to defend this but in the end withdraws it. It goes off the bottom edge towards gully on the bounce.
Short of a length down the leg side, Sharma hooks. It falls short of the fielder at backward square leg and the batters take one.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Another ball outside off, Sharma moves across and makes the leave.
Good length ball outside off, Sharma opts to leave again.
Good length ball on off, Sharma defends this one onto the ground.
Outside off, left alone by Sharma.
Down the leg side, Sharma looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards the man at point.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards point.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Leg bye! On the pads, Agarwal looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
Length ball outside off, Sharma is beaten and missed the line of the delivery.
EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball outside off, Sharma looks to cut but it flies off his outside edge between third slip and gully and into the third man fence.
Length ball on off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Length ball on middle and off, Agarwal cuts this one towards point.

EDGED AND FOUR! Mayank is riding his luck here and it may run out soon it seems. Good length ball outside off, nipping away. Agarwal looks to cut at it but the ball takes the outside edge, goes to the right of de Kock. He tries to dive and take it but misses. The ball hits the boot of Faf du Plessis at first slip and runs into the third man fence.
Agarwal chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Agarwal opens the face of his bat and guides this one towards backward point off the outer half of his bat.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, Sharma tries to flick this one towards the leg side but misses.
Length delivery outside off, nipping away. Sharma looks to defend and missed the line of the delivery.
On the pads of Sharma, he flicks this one towards fine leg for a couple.
Down the leg side, Sharma tries to flick but misses again.

OUT! CAUGHT! The man on a red-hot streak is out of here and the man who looked least likely to take a wicket since morning has done the trick. Length ball outside off by Rabada, Sharma looks to fend at this one. The ball goes off his outside edge and straight into the gloves of de Kock who will not drop those. One of the most potent threats to the visitors is out of here and this might just be the spark that Rabada needs to ignite himself after a dull morning so far.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Length ball outside off, Agarwal leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle and off, defended out by Agarwal.

FOUR LEG BYES! OUCH! That has hit Agarwal on the helmet! Short ball on middle and leg, Agarwal is late in ducking under it and is hit on the helmet. The ball flies over the keeper and into the fine keg fence but that will be a hard blow to Agarwal.

FOUR! Gorgeous! What a reply by Agarwal! Nortje bowls this one full and outside off, Agarwal leans forward and creams this one through covers for a boundary. Superb hand-eye co-ordination on that one.
Wide outside the off pole, left alone by Agarwal. End of an eventful over, 8 runs off the over.
No Ball! Rabada oversteps. Back of a length ball on off, Pujara starts his innings with a solid back foot defense.
Once again Rabada hits the deck hard. This one is a legitimate delivery though. Pujara defends it towards point off the outer half of his bat and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Good length ball on off, Pujara defends it towards mid on.

DROPPED! Tough chance but Bavuma is known to pluck these off at short leg but not on this occasion. Good length ball on the pads, Pujara flicks it uppishly straight towards short leg. The ball arrives quickly to Bavuma. It hits him on the grill of his helmet and comes down but unfortunately Temba fails to hold onto it. A life for Pujara. How costly will that prove to be?
Length ball just outside off, Pujara shows awareness of his off pole and leaves it alone.
On the pads, Pujara looks to flick but the ball goes off his thigh pad behind square on the leg side and they take a leg bye.
Another no ball. Once again Rabada oversteps his line. Length delivery on middle and leg, Agarwal defends it towards point.

Stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball on middle and leg, Mayank looks to defend but it hits him on the thigh pad. Rabada asks the question but the umpire is unmoved. Height seemed to be an issue.
Good length ball on the pads, Pujara tucks this one but straight to Bavuma at short leg. This time on the bounce though.
Good length ball on middle and off, Pujara plays this one off the front foot and into the ground.
Fullish outside off, Pujara blocks it out.
Another fuller one outside off, Pujara pushes this one towards cover. A little bit of yes and no games in the middle and in the end they decide against taking the run.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Pujara gets an inside edge and the ball hits him on the pads.
Length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Mayank.
Good length ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler by Agarwal.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards the man at cover by Agarwal.
Another one outside off, pushed towards cover again.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Mayank.
On the pads of Agarwal, he pushes this one towards square leg for a single.

FOUR! Shot of the day so far! Straight as an arrow, perfect hand-eye co-ordination, just a treat to the eyes! Full ball just outside off, Agarwal just gets on the front foot, pushes at this one and the ball races towards the fence down the ground.
FOUR! Another beautiful shot and Agarwal getting into the groove now. Full and wide outside off, leans into the drive and pushes this one towards the cover-point region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal defends this one off the back foot.
Length ball on middle and off, defended from within the crease.
FOUR! This time through the covers and third boundary of the over! Full and wide outside off, Agarwal drives this one through the cover region for a boundary.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
50 up for India! Down the leg side, Pujara flicks this one towards backward square leg and takes a single. India will be looking at this partnership to take them to a much more comfortable position.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards point.
Length ball on off, blocked onto the pitch.
This time a touch fuller, Agarwal pushes this one towards the off side.
Length ball just outside off, nipping back in. Agarwal covers the stumps and makes the leave.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal blocks this one out.
Length ball outside off, Pujara leaves this one alone.
Yorker by Nortje, a good nut! Pujara does well to jam it out.
Good length ball on middle and off, Pujara defends it from within the crease.
Length ball outside off, left alone by CP.

Full and wide outside off, Pujara pushes it towards cover and in the gap. The ball trudges towards the fence but does not have the legs to reach it. The fielder from cover hares after it and mops it up as the batters take three.

FOUR! Similar ball to the last one but Agarwal is in the sort of form that he will put those away 9 times out of 10. Full and wide outside off, Agarwal drives this through the gap at cover-point for a boundary.
Good length ball just outside off, Pujara defends this one towards point.
Another good length ball around off, pushed towards mid off.
On the pads of Pujara, he flicks it towards the man at deep backward square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Mayank.
Fullish ball just outside off, Agarwal pushes this one straight back towards Philander.
Length ball on off, Agarwal pushes this one towards point.
No ball! 4th No Ball of the day and all have come by Rabada. He needs to re-check his run up. Bowls this one full and on the pads, Pujara pushes this straight towards the man at mid on.
On the pads, Pujara flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Agarwal defends this one off the back foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Short of a length ball, Agarwal does well to stand tall and block it onto the pitch.
Length ball on middle and off, Agarwal defends it from within the crease onto the pitch.
Down the leg side, Mayank looks to flick this one towards the leg side but misses.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara defends it out.
Another one floated on the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Pujara takes the attack to Maharaj as he dances down the track. He flicks this one wide of mid-wicket, the fielder from mid-wicket gives it a chase but cannot keep the ball in play.
FOUR! Again Pujara dances down the track and drives this one through mid on. Another boundary for Pujara in this over. Not letting the spinner settle.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Rabada falls over! The landing area has been a problem for the bowlers and Rabada is feeling it. Delivers this one fuller, Agarwal pushes this one towards mid on. However, Rabada falls over in his followthrough.
Good length ball on middle, Mayank has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fullish around off, Agarwal defends this one off the front foot.
Length ball on middle and off, defended from within the crease.
Bouncer by Rabada to Agarwal, this time he ducks in time and evades it.

No foot movement and Mayank was beaten this time. Length ball around off, moving away. Agarwal looks to fend at it but gets beaten as he plays inside the line. Agarwal looks disappointed with himself.
Floated just outside off, Pujara defends this off the front foot.
Pujara dances down the track and flicks this one towards mid-wicket. Nortje there puts in a dive and stops the ball but the batters take a single in between a mix-up.
Shortish around off, the batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Floated on middle and off, Agarwal blocks this one out.
Agarwal shows the full face of the bat and blocks this one out.
Full and on off, Agarwal pushes this towards mid off. Maharaj dives to his left but misses however there is a backup in the deep so just a single.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Mayank.
Another one on middle and off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Good length ball on middle and off, Agarwal blocks this one out off the front foot.

Misfield! Good length delivery on off, Agarwal pushes this towards cover. It goes through the legs of Muthusamy and in the deep. The back up fielder runs from mid off mops it up near the fence and the batters take three.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Shortish on middle and off, Agarwal defends this off the back foot onto the pitch.
Length ball outside off, it spins back in. Agarwal is rooted to his crease. He looks to defend but the ball has taken the inside edge of the bat and thudded into his pads.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shortish outside off, punched off the  back foot towards the bowler.
Floated on middle and off, Agarwal blocks this one out.
Floated outside off, pushed towards short third man.
Good bouncer to start the over by Rabada. Near the off pole line, initially Pujara looks to play at it but sways away at the end.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

FOUR! On the pads, Pujara flicks this one towards mid-wicket with power. The fielder from mid on hares after it but is unable to keep it in play. This also brings up the 50-run stand between Agarwal and Pujara.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Length ball on middle and off, Pujara defends this one off the back foot.
Length ball just outside off, Pujara opens the face of his bat but it goes off the outside edge towards gully. It falls just short of the man there. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Keshav bowls a flighted delivery on off. Mayank gets on his front foot and defends it with confidence.
Shorter around off, Mayank punches it but straight towards cover.
Floated on the pads, Agarwal flicks it off the inner half of his bat towards the vacant short fine leg region and gets a couple.
Gives this one air on off, Mayank pushes it to cover.
On the stumps, Mayank keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Agarwal keeps  it out to get through the over unharmed.
Bowls it on the channel outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Outside off once again. Pujara has nothing to do with it.
Continues to bowl on the fourth stump line. Pujara continues to leave it alone.
Goes full and closer to the off pole. Pujara plants his front foot forward and blocks it.
Goes back to the fourth stump line. This one moves away off the deck. Pujara shoulders arms to it.
On middle and off, Pujara defends it to get through the over.
Maharaj tosses it up on middle, Mayank hits it back to the bowler off the inner half of his bat.
Flighted on the stumps, Mayank punches it to cover.
On the stumps, defended.
FOUR! Excellent use of the feet here from Mayank. Slightly overpitched on off, Mayank comes down the track a bit and smashes it through mid on for a boundary.
FOUR! Poor ball and rightfully punished. Overpitched on the pads, Mayank will have those for lunch as well. He whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
This time finds the fielder. Floated on off, Mayank drives it but straight to cover.
Good length ball on off, Che keeps it out.
FOUR! Glorious! Good length ball outside off, Pujara gets on his back foot, transfers the weight on it and punches it beautifully through cover-point for a boundary.
Sensibly follows the boundary with a calm leave outside his off stump.
On top of off, Che keeps it out.
Tempts Pujara to drive but he is in no mood to fall for that trap.
Way outside off, Pujara lets it carry to the keeper.
On the stumps, Agarwal keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Mayank defends it off the front foot.

Excitment and nothing else. Quicker one on middle and off, Mayank looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. There is a little excitment from the South African players but the umpire is unmoved.
Shorter around off, Mayank cuts it to point.
Flighted on off, MA pushes it to cover.
Loopy ball outside off, Agarwal leaves it alone.
Full around off, Pujara looks to defend it. It goes towards mid on off the inner half of his bat.
Full outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to it.
Continues to bowl in the channel outside off, Pujara is in no mood to disturb that.
Full around off, Cheteshwar pushes it to mid on.
Once again full and close to off, Pujara defends it to the on side.
Full and swinging away. Pujara pushes it with the swing towards mid off.
Drag down outside off as he sees Mayank come down the track. Agarwal still manages to punch it towards cover.
Floated on middle and leg, Mayank defends it to the on side.
Beauty! This one is floated around off, it spins and grips away after pitching. Agarwal looks to defend but misses. That was not too far away from the outside edge.
Beaten! Shorter outside off, Agarwal gets down on one knee and looks to play the late cut. The ball once again misses the outside edge of the bat by just a whisker.

What happened there? Flighted on off, Agarwal strokes it towards mid-wicket and looks for a single. Pujara is also in agreement but the bowler blocks him while he looks to take off. Luckily he manages to find a way and get to the other end without any casualty.
FOUR! Cut and cut in typical Pujara style. Short on middle and off, Pujara gets on his back foot and cuts it late through backward point for a boundary.
Full on off, Agarwal pushes it towards mid off.
Good length ball on the stumps, Mayank defends it off the back foot.
Full on off, Mayank drives it but cannot get it past the fielder at cover as the man there dives to his right and saves runs for his side.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Mayank defends it late to the off side.
Ohh! Full on middle, Mayank looks to defend but the ball nips in. It takes the inside edge of his bat and goes behind square on the leg side for a single.
Length delivery on off, Pujara keeps it out to get through the over.
Flighted on off, Mayank keeps it out.
Bounce on this one. It is short on off, it shoots up. Mayank defends it off the upper half of his bat towards point.
Gives this one air on off, Agarwal blocks it.

FIFTY FOR MAYANK AGARWAL! He continues his impressive run in Tests. Short around off, Mayank slams it through point for a boundary. He raises his bat as the crowd and his teammates applaud his knock. Agarwal will now look to convert this into a hundred. Brings up the 100 for India too.
Follows it up with a very calm front foot defense.
On the stumps, kept out by MA.
Bouncer! Nortje starts his new spell with the effort ball. It is around the body but down the leg side. Cheteshwar ducks under it.
Another short one. Once again Pujara sits under it. This is further down the leg side. Anrich needs to correct his line if he wants to trouble the batter with these short stuff.
Full on off, Cheteshwar defends it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Pujara tucks it to backward square leg.
Another short one. This is outside off, Pujara sways away from it.
On the body, Pujara tucks it towards square leg. Maiden for Nortje to start off his new spell.
Tossed up outside off, pushed towards the off side.
Floated outside off, pushed to the man at short cover.
Tossed up on the fourth stump line, pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter on off, pushed towards the bowler again.
Shortish outside off, cut towards cover-point for a single.
On the pads, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Nortje still bowling quick, at 141.2 kph. Agarwal flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Bouncer down the leg side, Pujara ducks under it.
Length ball on middle and leg, Pujara pushes it towards short mid on off the back foot.
Length ball on middle and off, Pujara defends it from within the crease.

A mix up again but luckily no harm done! Shorter delivery outside off, Pujara cuts this one towards cover-point. The man there runs after it and mops it up. There is a chance for the third but Pujara is not interested with Agarwal halfway down the track. However, the throw is at the keeper's end and that allows Agarwal to get back in as de Kock has a shy at the bowler's end. The bowler fails to collect the ball and the ball rolls towards mid on. Now Pujara wants a run but Mayank refuses. These two need to sort things out in their running.
Pujara works it down the leg side.
Short of a length outside off, Agarwal drives it towards point for a couple.
Another one, a touch short, Agarwal cuts it towards cover-point and takes a single.
Fuller on the pads, pushed towards mid on.
On the pads again, flicked towards mid on for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and floated outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards long off for a single.
On the pads, Agarwal flicks it towards the leg side.
Bouncer down the leg side, Agarwal gets under it.

FOUR! Bouncer again but this time Agarwal does not shy away! Down the leg side, Agarwal gets on top of the bounce and rolls his wrists as he hooks this one all along the ground towards the fine leg boundary. However, this is a risky shot as there is a leg gully and a deep fine leg in place and the South African players are trying to lure Agarwal into that shot.
Bouncer outside off, Agarwal leaves it alone.
On the pads, Agarwal flicks this one down the leg side for a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Floated on off, Mayank keeps it out.
Shorter on off and middle, Mayank guides it towards point with a flat bat.
Once again slightly short, Mayank tucks it to the right of short leg.
This one bounces off the surface. It is on off, Mayank defends it off the upper half of his bat.
Floated on off, Mayank drives it straight to the man at catching position at short extra cover.
Once again drives it straight to the man at extra cover.
Bouncer around off, Pujara sways away from it.
Hits the deck hard on off, Pujara comfortably taps it back to the bowler.
Back of a length on the body, Che tucks it towards square leg.
Good length delivery on off, Pujara nudges it towards point and gets one.
Comes around the wicket to Agarwal and bangs it in short. Agarwal ducks under it.
Another short one. Mayank once again goes under the ball.
Floated on off, Pujara keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Cheteshwar defends it to the on side.
Floated on off, Pujara comes down the track and whips it but finds square leg.
On off, Pujara keeps it out.
On middle, Pujara comes down the track and whips it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! He was looking to pierce the gap on the leg side and after finding the fielder on the previous two occasions, he has finally managed to get it. On the pads, Pujara comes down the track and whips it behind square on the leg side to get a boundary.

FOUR! One trick too many maybe. Another short ball, Mayank gets on his back foot and hooks it through backward square leg for a boundary. He was not in complete control of that but he won't mind it. Partnership now moves to 99 with that.
On the pads, Agarwal flicks it to square leg.

FOUR! Pulled with power, aggression and control. Short ball on off, Mayank transfers his weight onto his back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Brings up the 100-run stand in style.
Once again short, Mayank this time pulls it just wide of mid-wicket for one.
Good length ball around off, Pujara looks to play it on the off side but it goes back to the bowler off the edge of his bat.
On the pads, Pujara tucks it fine down the leg side and keeps the strike.
Floated on off, Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Pujara flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.

Misfield and they get a quick single. Short on off, Pujara guides it towards point. Rabada misfields and they set off for a quick single. De Bruyn gets to the ball and sends an ordinary throw at the keeper's end. Quinton looks to flick it onto the stumps but misses.
On the stumps, Agarwal keeps it out.
Floated on off, Agarwal strokes it towards cover for a run.
On the stumps, Puji defends it off the front foot.
Starts with a floated ball on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot.
A very good start is followed by a drag down. Short outside off, Mayank punches it to deep cover for one. Senuran is lucky that it is just a one.
Floated on middle, Pujara blocks it away.

Excellent ball. Muthusamy bowls it slower on off and middle. Pujara looks to defend but the ball grips and turns away beating the outside edge of Cheteshwar's  willow. First ball that has actually spun today.
SIX! A very impressive ball is followed by a sub-par delivery. Short on middle and leg, Pujara gets on his back foot and whacks it over the mid-wicket fence for the first maximum of the game.
Once again short, this time Pujara cuts it towards point and keeps the strike.
On the pads, Pujara turns it to square leg.
Floated on middle, Cheteshwar keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Pujara glances it towards square leg and looks for one but Mayank sends him back.
Gives it air on middle, Che glances it to mid-wicket.
Turn and bounce. Short outside off, Pujara gets on his back foot to punch it through the off side but the ball spins away and Cheteshwar after looking at that retracts  from the shot.
Normalcy restored as this tossed up ball is kept out by CP.
Short on middle, Agarwal pushes it back to the bowler.
Once again it is short on off, Mayank taps it to point.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
FOUR! Poor ball. Drag down on the pads, Agarwal pulls it with ease through mid-wicket to fetch himself another boundary.
On the stumps, Agarwal blocks it away.
Flighted on off, Mayank milks it to long off and keeps the strike.
On the pads, Mayank looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Short around off, Agarwal guides it down to short third man.
Floated on off and middle, Mayank comes down the track and looks to hit it straight down the ground but it comes off the lower half of his bat and goes straight to Keshav.
Short around off, Mayank cuts it towards point and gets to the other end.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Sharp turn. Flighted on off, Pujara looks to defend but the ball spins away off the deck missing the outside edge and the off pole by only a fraction.
Starts with a good length ball around off, Mayank keeps it out.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal blocks it.
Length delivery around off, Mayank square drives it to point.
Full on off, MA pushes it to cover.
Full on middle, Agarwal pushes it to mid on.
Full around off, Mayank strokes it wide of sweeper cover for a couple.
Flighted on off, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards square leg.
Tossed up on off, Pujara blocks it.

FOUR! Excellent use of the feet. Floated on middle, Pujara comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and whips it between mid-wicket and mid on for a boundary. 150 up for India with this boundary.
Follows it up with a calm front foot defense.

FOUR! Pujara gets to his fifty in style. Short around off, Pujara gets on his back foot and cuts it with grace through point for a boundary. Back-to-back fifties for Cheteshwar. He raises his bat as the crowd applaud his knock. He was dropped on 0 and he has made full use of it.
On the stumps, Pujara comes down the track and keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, pushed back towards Rabada.
On the pads, Mayank flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full one on off, Pujara looks to defend but it comes off the inside half of the bat and goes on to hit the pads.
On the pads again, full ball. Pujara flicks this one towards mid-wicket again and takes a couple. That has been a very busy zone in Pujara's innings.
FOUR! Punched with ease! Back of a length ball on off, Pujara just stands tall and punches this off his toes towards the point region for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket right near the end of the second session of play and just what the doctor ordered for South Africa! Rabada is the man again to give the visitors a breakthrough. Bowls it on a length just outside off, it nips back in. Pujara is stuck in his crease and on the back foot. He tries to defend it but the ball goes off the outside edge low towards the left of first slip. Faf du Plessis, the South African skipper there makes no mistake there as he takes a very difficult catch. He is down on the ground after taking the catch almost in relief. A very important breakthrough for the Proteas as they break the 138-run stand.
Short outside off, Mayank cuts it to the man at point.
Short around off, Agarwal punches it towards cover and gets a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Kohli starts his innings with a solid front foot defense.
Beauty! Tossed up outside off, Kohli gets on his front foot to defend this but it turns away just a bit. Enough to beat the outside edge of Kohli's willow.
This time Kohli gets right behind the ball and keeps it down.
On the stumps, Virat lunges forward and blocks it to get through the over.
Bouncer! A well directed one too. It is closer to the body. Agarwal though gets under it.
Length delivery on the pads, Mayank glances it towards mid-wicket and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Outside off, Mayank does not disturb it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Rabada is finding his steam back. Hits the deck hard on off and middle and makes the ball shape in. Mayank looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes between first slip and gully for a boundary. Would have been interesting to see if it would have carried to second slip if that was there.
Length delivery on off, Mayank keeps it out.
Fuller on off, MA pushes it to cover and that will Tea on Day 1.
Beauty to start with! Flighted outside off, Virat looks to defend but the ball spins away beating Kohli all ends up.
The Indian skipper is off the mark. On the pads, Virat glances it towards square leg and gets to the other end.
Short outside off, Mayank cuts it towards point and rotates the strike.
Shorter on off, Kohli defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Virat keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, VK defends it to get through the first over after the break unharmed.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal comes on the front foot and blocks it to the cover region.
Plays the ball straight to the cover fielder.
On off again, Agarwal plays off his front foot towards mid off.
Back of a length, generates extra bounce, Agarwal off the back foot plays it to the off side.
Floated on off, MA covers the line of the ball and pokes it to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Mayank drives it to mid off. No run.
On off, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on the stumps, Virat lunges forward and defends it.
Good shot but also brilliant stop from Muthusamy. Floated on middle and leg, Virat drives it wide of mid on. Senuran Muthusamy runs to his right and saves a certain boundary with a dive.
Shorter on off, Agarwal punches it to cover.

SIX! This one is out of here. Flighted on off, Mayank comes down the track and smashes it over long off for a maximum. Gets into the 90s with that. Six to get into the 90s, well this is Sehwag-esque from the young Karnataka batter.
SIX! Make that two in a row. Agarwal just one short of a well-deserved ton. Floated on off and middle, Agarwal comes down the track and smashes it over the bowler's head for another biggie.
Full outside off, Kohli comes on the front and blocks it towards mid off.
Angled into the batsman, Kohli woks it to square leg for a single. Agarwal on strike, he is on 99.
Angled too far across, Agarwal lets it pass to de Kock down the leg side.

CENTURY FOR MAYANK AGARWAL! This has been an excellent knock from the young batter. 200 in the first innings of the first Test and another century here. He has made that opening slot his. Good length ball outside off, Mayank looks to cut but it goes off the outer half of his bat wide of the man at gully. The fielder there dives but cannot get close to the ball and it races away to the fence. He fist pumps the air in delight. He removes his helmet and has a big, joyful hug with his skipper. Take a bow, young man!
Plays the ball towards deep cover for a single.
Good length ball, angling into Kohli, who looks to drive but it goes off the inside half of the bat to mid on.
Floated on off, Agarwal strokes it towards point for one.
Tossed up on off, Virat defends it off the front foot.

Has Maharaj dropped Kohli here? Oh yes, he has. Tough chance but certainly a chance. Slower through the air on off, Kohli hits it hard and straight. But he also hits it uppishly straight back towards the bowler. Keshav gets down to his left and gets his fingertips to it. Unfortunately for him he cannot hold onto it. The ball goes behind to long off and the batsmen take a single.
On the stumps, Mayank keeps it out.
Flights one on off, MA pushes it to cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a good length outside off, Kohli comes forward to defend the ball.
Fuller on on off, Kohli cover the line to block the ball.
Good length outside off again, Kohli comes far forward on the front foot to play it to the covers.
Goes on the back foot to not such a short ball to punch it to short cover.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
On a good length, Philander get the ball to come back in with the angle. Kohli on his front foot to defend the ball, works it from the inside half of the bat to mid on.
Gives this one air around off, Mayank looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of his bat wide of first slip for one.
On the stumps, Kohli defends it with confidence.
FOUR! Nobody moves. Maharaj gets his length wrong as he drags it short and wide outside off. Kohli gets on his back foot and slashes it through point for a boundary.
Tossed up on the stumps, Kohli blocks it.
On the pads, Virat flicks it to square leg.
Short and on the pads, Kohli whips it to the man at mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Agarwal is firmly behind it to defend it.
Short outside off, Agarwal camps on the back foot and plays the ball late to deep point for a couple.
Agarwal shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, comes in a tad, Agarwal safely lets it go to the keeper.
Plays the ball on the front foot to the cover region.

OUT! The centurion has been dismissed by none other than the sole wicket-taker of the day, Kagiso Rabada! It was a good length ball, which was angled into Agarwal, it pitched and straightened a bit. Mayank had committed to the shot and the ball went off the outside edge to first slip. Just like his last wicket, the skipper of South Africa, Faf du Plessis at first slip takes a good catch. Mayank Agarwal walks off the pitch to a standing ovation from the crowd and the players. A great knock by him comes to an end.
Floated outside off, pushed towards cover.
Flatter outside off, left alone by Virat Kohli.
On the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
On the pads again, pushed towards the man at short mid on.
Floated outside off, pushed towards the off side.
Another one full and floated outside off, Kohli pushes this one towards cover.
Bouncer outside off, Rahane sways away from it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rahane gets on top of the bounce and keeps it down.
Full ball outside off, swings in and  de Kock collects it to his left.
On the pads, Rahane clips it to the on side.
Outside off, Rahane pushes the ball to the covers.
Short ball around off, Rahane was about to pull the ball but he misses the shot. The ball his the grill of his helmet. Umpire Chris Gaffaney calls out to the Indian team physio to check on Rahane.
Floated on the stumps, Kohli keeps it out.
On stumps, defended.
Floated on off, Kohli pushes it to cover.
On the pads, Kohli flicks it to square leg.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman.
Floated on off, Kohli strokes it towards point and keeps the strike.
Good length ball, outside off, it swings in after pitching, de Kock collects.
Kohli stays on the back foot and plays the ball to gully.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Short ball on middle and leg, Kohli pulls and sets off for a single. He checks his run as Rabada is blocking his way. May be to avoid yet another fine! 200 comes up for India.
On a good length on off, Rahane gets properly behind the line of the ball and plays it to mid off.
Fullish ball on off, Rahane works it to point.
Floated on the stumps, Kohli strokes it back to the bowler.
On the pads, Kohli turns it to square leg.
Tossed up on the stumps, Virat calmly blocks it.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! School boy stuff from Rabada. Completely unnecessary. Flighted on off, Virat nudges it wide of point and takes a single. Rabada gets to the ball and sends a wild throw, way wide of the keeper. The batters don't even bother running the second because there is no backup and are completely sure that it will go to the fence.
Gives this air around off, Rahane keeps it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short ball around off, Kohli goes on his toes to defend the ball.
Again blocks the short ball off the back foot to the off side.

FOUR! A lucky escape for Kohli.  Short and fast delivery angled into Kohli, it gets too high on him after bouncing. He went for a pull but the ball went off the the gloves just wide of de Kock to the fine leg fence.
Shortish ball, defended off the back foot.
Kohli shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full ball outside off, Kohli plays it to point.
Floated on off, Rahane keeps it out off the inner half of his bat to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Ajinkya looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up on off, Ajinkya defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Rahane strokes it to point.
On the stumps, Rahane keeps it out.
The batsman drives this through the covers.
FOUR! Pulled with power. Back of a length ball on off, Kohli gets on his back foot and pulls it with venom through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Kohli tries to turn the ball to the on side but it goes off the leading edge of his bat.
On the pads of Kohli, clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Full on middle and leg again Rahane wristily flicks the ball to the mid-wicket boundary.
On the pads yet again Rahane stands tall to clip it to mid on. No run.
Another short ball, Rahane looks to pull but gets a bottom edge towards mid on. A quick single taken.
Floated on middle and off, Rahane keeps it out.
Drifts one on middle and leg, Rahane looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge towards backward point.
Tossed up on off, Ajinkya defends it off the front foot.
Gives this one air on middle, Ajinkya defends it with calmness.
On off, AR is in no hurry and defends it with ease.
Shorter on off, Rahane cuts it to the man at point.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery outside off, Virat drives it towards mid off.
On the fourth stump line, Virat leaves it alone.
Bouncer! Kohli ducks under it.
Fuller on off, Kohli looks to drive but only gets a bottome edge.
Flighted on off, Rahane keeps it out.
On the stumps, AR blocks it off.
Shorter on off, Rahane punches it to the man at cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Gives this air on middle, Ajinkya defends it to the on side.
Floated on off, Rahane defends it to get through another over.
Flighted on off, Kohli pushes it to cover.
Beauty! Muthusamy gives this air on off, it spins away after pitching. Kohli looks to defend but gets squared up.
Tossed up on off, Virat blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Virat strokes it towards long off and gets an easy single.
Another calm front foot defense from Rahane.
Slightly quicker on off and middle, Rahane looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
Shorter on off, Kohli punches it towards backward point. Kohli looks for a risky single but Rahane rightfully sends him back.
Tossed up on off, Virat pushes it back to the left of the bowler.
Darted around the pads, Kohli turns it to square leg for one.
Flighted on the stumps, Rahane shows his composure and blocks it.
On the stumps and once again Rahane blocks it.
Loopy ball on middle, AR defends it to get through the over.
Tossed up outside off, Kohli strides out and defends.
Pulls the length back a bit and it's slower though the air. Kohli off the back foot works it to the on side for a single.
Rahane comes on the front foot and defends it.
No ball! Flighted outside off, Rahane defends it to covers off the front foot.
Goes on the back foot and guides the ball towards gully.
Another front foot defense by Rahane.
Floats it in on middle and leg, Rahane drives it to mid on.
Floated on the stumps, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Short, wide and punished. Maharaj bowls it short outside off, Kohli gets on his back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Flighted on off, Kohli drives it on the up but straight to the man at cover.
Flighted on off, Kohli keeps it out.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! Floated on middle and off, Kohli whips it through mid-wicket. Bavuma gives it a chase and puts a desperate dive to save it but he comes second in the race.
Floated on off, Kohli milks it to cover and keeps the strike.
Floated on middle and off, Kohli drives it to long off for a single.
Rahane stays on the back foot and waits for the ball to turn. He blocks it in the end.
FOUR! Short ball outside off, Rahane looks to cut it but he doesn't middle it. It runs away to the third man fence for a boundary.
No ball! He covered the line of the ball and defended it. Muthusamy overstepped for the second time.
Stays in his crease and defends the ball.
Floated outside off, Rahane blocks it to point.
Ajinkya stays on the back foot and lets the ball pass to the keeper.
FOUR! Part-timer gets a harsh welcome. Elgar starts with a drag down around off. Kohli's eyes lit up looking at that. He pulls it with sheer power through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Kohli angles it towards short third man.
Another drag down but this one is punched straight to cover.
Floated on off, Kohli pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Kohli milks it to long off and gets to the other end.
Around off, Rahane strokes it to cover and keeps the strike.
On the pads, Rahane tucks it to square leg.
Tossed up on the stumps, Ajinkya defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on off, Rahane lunges forward and defends it.
Tossed up on off, AR blocks it.
Slightly shorter on off, Ajinkya defends it.
On the stumps, Ajinkya blocks it.
Elgar tosses it up on middle, Kohli comes inside out and plays the ball to long off for a couple. The long off fielder does well to keep it down.
Floated outside off, it's played through the covers for a single.
Full outside off, Rahane played it to the off side.
Camps  on the back foot and opens the face of the bat late to guide it to third man for a couple of runs. The 50-run stand comes up.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Defends the ball off the back foot to the off side.

Stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball on off, it nips back in. Kohli looks to defend but it hits him high on the pad. Philander is the only one going up in his appeal. He later suggests it is too high and they do not take the review. Replay then rolls and Ultra Edge shows that there was a slight inside edge as well.
Fuller on off it shapes in. Kohli looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
FOUR! Bad ball and rightfully punished. You cannot bowl on the pads of Kohli and Philander has just done that. Virat eases his flick through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full on middle and leg, Kohli defends it towards mid on.

FOUR! Kohli gets his fifty in style. Good length ball on off, Kohli gets on his front foot and creams his drive through covers to bring up his 23rd Test fifty. The skipper has taken his time and has hardly been troubled. He will be looking to convert this into a big one.
Length delivery outside off, Virat leaves it alone.
With the new cherry, Rabada hurls in a back of a length delivery around off. Rahane goes on his toes to defend the ball but it goes off the inside edge and on to the thigh pad.
Same line and length it moves in after pitching and Rahane gets another inside edge onto the pads. This time he is able to cross over for a single.
Angles it too far down the leg side. Kohli misses his flick shot.
On a good length outside off, Kohli shoulders arms.
Outside off, let alone.
Same line as the last two deliveries, Kohli deals with it the same way. It's left alone.
Good length delivery around off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Full around off, Rahane defends it towards cover and shouts 'no, no' to his partner.
Good length ball on middle, Rahane looks to flick it but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards fine leg for one.

FOUR! Lucky or intentional? Length ball outside off, Kohli looks to play at it but then decides to leave it. He is too late in his decision though as the ball still hits the lower half of his bat and goes through second slip and gully for a boundary.
Fuller on off, Kohli strokes it towards extra cover. The fielder there deflects the ball towards mid off and they take a single.
Outside off, no worries for Rahane as he leaves it alone.
Fuller outside off, Kohli jumps up with the bounce and plays the ball to deep point for a single.
It's bowled full on off, that's firmly defended off the front foot by Rahane.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rahane lets it pass to the keeper.
Length ball on middle and leg, Rahane plays it to mid-wicket.
Defended off the back foot by Rahane.
Length delivery on off, Kohli tucks it to square leg.
On the fourth stump line, Kohli leaves it.
FOUR! CLASS! Overpitched on off, Kohli drives it between cover and mid off. Finding the gap to perfection and finds the fence.
Good comeback! Length ball around off, Kohli goes chasing after it but the ball zips away after pitching, beating the outside edge of his bat.
On the stumps, VK defends it with authority.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
FOUR! Short and angled into the batsman at 145.4 kph, Rahane goes for the pull but misses, it takes the top edge and runs over the keeper to the fine leg fence. It has gone really dark in the middle.
Good length ball to start off the day, jagging back in. Rahane gets his bat down just in time to keep the ball out as he inside edges it onto the pads.
Jaffa this one! Length delivery just outside off, nipping away from Rahane. He tries to feel it but does so inside the line. The ball beats his outside edge and whizzes towards de Kock.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards cover off the back foot by Rabada.
Length ball on the off pole line, pushed back towards Rabada by Ajinkya.
No ball! Rabada oversteps in the first over of Day 2. Bowls a rank one down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but can't get his bat on it.
Good length ball just outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Good length ball, nipping back in. Kohli looks to defend this one but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg for a single. Kohli off the mark on Day 2.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Rahane.
Good length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards Vernon by Rahane.
Length ball outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane pushes it off the back foot towards point.
Good leave by Rahane to end the over. Not getting lured into the drive to this full delivery outside off.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Virat.
Another ball way outside off by Rabada, Kohli has no interest in playing at that.
Outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to let that one through. The Protea bowlers need to get their lines and lengths right.
Fourth ball in a row outside off, left alone by VK.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Kohli defends this one with perfect timing back past the bowler and the batters take one as the fielder from mid on mops it up.
Rahane defends this one off the front foot towards the off side.
Good length ball on the off pole line, Kohli blocks it out.
Length ball outside off by Philander, Kohli lets it through to de Kock.
BEATEN! Jaffa by Philander now! Length ball on the fourth stump line, it pitches and nips away with some extra bounce. Kohli looks to initially play at it but withdraws his bat at the last moment.
Good length delivery around the off pole line, Kohli pushes this one towards mid off.
Length ball outside off, Kohli lets it be.

EDGED AND FOUR! Almost, almost Philander did the trick for South Africa here! Bowls a good length delivery in the corridor of uncertainty. Kohli has a poke at this one with soft hands and outside edges it towards the keeper but it is just wide of de Kock's right hand. It goes from underneath his gloves towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Rahane shoulders arms to let that one through.
Rahane defends this one off the front foot by presenting the full face of the bat towards mid off.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards the point region.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads of Rahane, he flicks this one towards square leg and takes a single.
Kohli shoulders arms to let that one through to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Another one outside off, Rahane shoulders arms.
Much closer to the off pole this time but Rahane knows exactly where his stumps are and makes a confident leave.
Outside off, left alone by Ajinkya.
Five balls, all of them left alone by Rahane. South Africa need to make the Indian batters play.
Finally a ball played off the bat! Length ball outside off, pushed towards point by Rahane.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli pushes this one towards point.
Too wide outside off, Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Length ball outside off, Kohli chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full length ball outside off, Kohli pushes this one with firm hands straight to the man at cover.
Good length ball on middle and off, Kohli pushes this one towards the bowler.
FOUR! First intentional boundary of the day and it comes off the bat of the skipper! Full on middle and leg, Kohli punches this one fiercely, down the ground, through mid on for a boundary.

EDGED AND FOUR! How unlucky can Philander be? Another beauty by him, pitching this one fullish and a touch outside off, Rahane looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball flies towards the left of the gully fielder, Aiden Markram who dives but cannot get to it. The ball flies to the third man fence for a boundary.
On the pads, Rahane works this one towards square leg for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball on off, he pushes this one towards point.
Full ball outside off, Kohli drives it towards cover. Bavuma runs towards it and puts in a dive to keep it down to a single. Good fielding this by the young South African.
Good length ball angling in. Rahane looks to defend it but it comes off the inside edge and onto the pads.
Short of a length ball just outside off, Kohli goes for a rash cut shot but does not connect.
Fullish ball just outside off, pushed towards the man at cover.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Good length ball just outside off, Kohli looks to fend at it with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge but falls short of Faf du Plessis at second slip.
FOUR! Pulls and pulls hard at it! Shortish ball on middle and leg, Kohli rocks back and pulls this one through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
Wide outside off, left alone by Kohli.
Good length ball on the off pole line, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball just outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder by Rahane.
On the off side, Rahane pushes this one towards point for one.
Another one outside off, Kohli pushes this one towards point again.
Fullish ball outside off, pushed towards the man at mid off.
Outside off by Philander, Kohli dabs it near the pitch on the off side.
Good fielding by Markram, like a goalkeeper! Short of a length ball outside off, Rahane cuts this one towards the right of gully where Markram dives and saves a certain boundary of his side.
Length ball on middle and off, Rahane rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball towards cover for a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, Kohli defends this off the back foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

100 partnership up between Kohli and Rahane and this is the 10th time they have achieved this milestone. Some consistency one must say! On the pads of Kohli, he flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single. A very important partnership for the Indians this.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! On the pads of Kohli, he flicks it away towards square leg for a boundary. Great batting by the Indian skipper here.
Length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
No ball! Rabada oversteps for the 6th time in this match. Full ball on off, Kohli pushes this one towards extra cover.
Rahane tries to defend this one but gets the bottom edge onto the pitch.
On the pads, Rahane flicks this one straight towards the man at square leg.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends this one off the back foot.
FOUR! On the pads again, Rahane flicks this one nicely between the gap at square leg and fine leg for a boundary.
Kohli pushes this one off the front foot towards the cover region for a single.
FOUR! Elegant shot by Rahane! Short of a length ball outside off, Rahane gets onto his toes and cuts this one towards backward point for a boundary.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
BEATEN! Beauty by Nortje! Bangs it hard on the surface, Rahane looks to get on top of the bounce and play but the ball whizzes past his outside edge due to the movement on it.
Short of a length ball outside off, Rahane gets onto the back foot and pulls this one towards backward square leg for a single.
Kohli defends this one from within the crease.
Length ball outside off, Rahane cuts this one towards the man at point.
Good length delivery on off, Rahane blocks this one off the back foot.
Outside off again, Rahane pushes this one towards the off side.
On middle and off, Rahane pushes it back to the bowler.
Length ball on middle and off, Rahane blocks this one off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on middle and leg, Rahane pushes this one off the back foot towards mid on.
Back of a length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone. De Kock behind the stumps fails to gather it but it does not cost any run.
Gets his length a little bit further. This one tails in a bit, Kohli defends it to the off side.

Beaten! Length delivery outside off, Kohli goes fishing for the delivery outside off. The ball though keeps a bit low and goes past Kohli's edge. A rare lapse of concentration for Virat in this innings.
Good length delivery on off, Kohli taps it towards cover-point and gets to the other end.

FOUR! Classic Rahane cut! Length ball around off, Ajinkya gets on his back foot and cuts it with class through point for a boundary. He is getting into his groove now. Rahane had to battle for his run early on but now he is getting it.
Another cut but this is just wide of point so just a single.

SAFE! The pitching looked to be an issue and it turns out to be the actual issue. South Africa lose one of their 2 reviews. Flighted around leg, Rahane looks to defend but the ball spins in beating his defense. The ball hits him on the back pad. The South African players put in a loud appeal but the umpire turns it down. Faf has a word with his bowler and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge first confirms no involvement of bat. Ball Tracker then comes in and it shows the ball is pitching outside leg. Excellent umpiring this. Rahane survives!
Calmly taps this one back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Rahane blocks it away.
On the stumps, AR calmly blocks it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted on the off, Ajinkya cuts it to the man at point.

FOUR! Kohli gets into the nervous 90s in a nervous looking way. Nortje steams in and hits the deck hard around off, Virat looks to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge and flies low and wide of second slip for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Virat defends it with soft hands towards cover for one.
On the stumps, Rahane blocks it astutely.
Good length delivery on off, Rahane gets on his front foot and defends it classically.
Around the pads, Rahane turns it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Excellent ball. Yorker on middle and leg, Kohli jams it out towards mid on.
Flighted on off, Rahane lunges forward and blocks it.
Show of aggression from Ajinkya. Floated on off and middle, Rahane comes down the track and hits it towards long on for a single. He did not time the ball well though there.
Tossed up on off, Kohli strokes it to mid off.
Gives this one air on off, Kohli plants his front foot forward and defends it.
Looped up on off, Virat milks it to long off and calmly gets to the other end.
On the pads, AR turns it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball around off, Kohli gets on his back foot and punches it on the up towards point for one.
Slightly fuller on middle and off, Rahane gets across and defends it towards mid on.
Good length ball around off, Rahane defends it with a straight bat towards mid on.
Short ball on off, Rahane pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Fuller around off, Rahane pushes it to cover.
Length delivery on off, Rahane taps it towards cover-point and looks for a quick run. Kohli though sends him back and rightfully so as that would have been very risky.
Good stop! Floated on middle and leg, Kohli whips it to the right of short mid-wicket. The fielder there dives to his right and saves runs for his side. Keeping it down to one.
Tossed up on off, Rahane blocks it.
Shorter on middle and leg, Rahane punches it to the on side.
Flighted on off, Ajinkya strokes it to point.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Short around off, Rahane gets on his back foot, waits for the ball to turn and then cuts it with it through point. Theunis de Bruyn gives it a chase and tries to pull it back with a dive but he fails to do so.
Follows it up with a gentle nudge towards long on for one.

FIFTY FOR RAHANE! He has had to work really hard for this but after taking his time he has looked solid and got into his own. Good length ball on off, Rahane gets across and tucks it to the on side to get to his 20th Test fifty. He raises his bat as the crowd applaud his effort. There were questions regarding his place before the West Indies tour but since that tour the Indian Test vice captain  has answered his critics with solid performances.
Fuller on off and middle, Kohli pushes it to mid on.
On the fourth stump line, Kohli leaves it alone.
Length ball, Kohli defends it towards cover.
Anrich steams in and hits the deck hard on off, Kohli blocks it with minimum of fuss.
Good length ball around off, Kohli gets on his back foot and punches it with authority towards point and keeps the strike.
Tossed up on middle, Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Kohli strokes it to mid on.

Oh! Maharaj getting some help from this end. Slightly shorter outside off, Kohli looks to cut it but the ball comes quicker and goes between the bat and body, missing the inside edge by just a fraction.
Floated on middle, Kohli nudges it wide of mid on. Muthusamy runs across and dives to his left, keeping it down to one.
Gives this air on off, Rahane drives it to mid off.
Short around off, AR cuts it but to the man at point.
Shorter around off, Kohli dabs it towards short third man.
Floated on the stumps, Virat defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on middle, Kohli gets on his back foot and punches it to mid on.
Short again, this is on off.  Kohli gets on his back foot and punches it to the off side this time for one. Moves to 97 with that.
Better from Senuran. Gives it air and bowls fuller on off, Rahane defends it with a straight bat.
Tossed up around off, Rahane lunges forward and blocks it to get through the over.
Starts his new spell with a good length ball on off. Kohli pushes it to cover-point.
Length ball outside off, Kohli offers a good leave to it.
Length ball around off, Kohli defends it.

HUNDRED FOR VIRAT KOHLI! Captaining in his 50th Test, the skipper has marked this occasion with a delicious century. The world's best batsman is back doing what he does best, scoring tons. Full ball on middle and leg, Kohli plays a glamorous on drive to get to the milestone. He removes his helmet and raises his bat as the fans and his teammates applaud his terrific knock. Surprisingly, this is Kohli's first Test ton in 2019! Number 26 in Tests! Can he convert this into a double hundred?
On the fourth stump line, Virat leaves it alone.
On the stumps, Kohli keeps it out.
Shorter on the middle pole line, tucket towards mid-wicket.
Full and floated on off, pushed towards the cover-point region.
Muthusamy bowls it down the leg side, Rahane gets down on one knee and sweeps this one fine towards the leg side for a couple.
Full and floated on middle and leg, pushed back towards the bowler.
Outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Floated delivery on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Kohli keeps it out.
Full ball on off, Virat defends it towards cover.
Full on middle, Kohli tucks it wide of mid on and gets a single to bring up the 150-run stand between the duo.
Good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it with a straight bat.
Length ball around off, Rahane defends it late off his front foot.
Philander maintains his line and bowls it fuller. Ajinkya defends it.
Bowls it slower through the air on middle, Kohli defends it off the inner half of his bat to the on side.
Slightly shorter on middle, Kohli turns it towards square leg and gets to the other end.
Tossed up on middle and off, Virat pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter on off and middle, Rahane whips it through square leg and takes three as Theunis de Bruyn cleans it up before the ropes. 350 comes up for India with that.
Loopy ball on the stumps, Kohli lunges forward and blocks it.
Shorter on off, Kohli punches it towards cover-point and looks for a run but Rahane says no.
Markram starts with a wild ball. Way outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Markram corrects his line  and bowls it closer to the off pole, Rahane strokes it through point for a couple.
Shorter around off, Rahane cuts it towards backward point. Philander dives and saves runs for his side. However, the batters are able to take a single.

Direct hit and Rahane might have been back to the pavilion. Flighted on off, Kohli defends it with soft hands towards cover and calls for a quick single. Rahane responds. Bavuma gets to the ball quickly and sends it at the keeper's end. Rahane puts in a desperate dive to get back in and Bavuma misses his shy at the stumps by just a whisker.
Shorter on off, Ajinkya keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Rahane keeps it out and that will be Lunch on Day 2.
Senuran starts with a flatter delivery outside off. Kohli lunges forward and leaves it alone.
Floated on middle, Kohli plants his front foot forward and blocks it.
Shorter on middle, Kohli this time shows his back foot defense.
Musthusamy continues to bowl short. This is outside off, Virat cuts it through point for a couple.
On the pads, Virat flicks it to the on side and gets to the other.
First ball after Lunch for Rahane. He resumes his innings with a solid front foot defense.
Fuller on off and middle, Kohli turns it to square leg.
FOUR! Creamed! One of the toughest shot to play in cricket and Kohli does it with ease. Full on off and middle, Virat gets on his front foot and plays the on drive to perfection for a boundary.
Good length ball which zips back in. Kohli looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! WOW! This is just a batting masterclass! Slightly overpitched on middle by Rabada. He could have got away with it had he bowled it to some other batsman but not to Kohli. He gets on his front foot and plays another crisp on drive for a boundary.
Kohli now shows his defensive skill and blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller on off, Kohli blocks it to get through the over.
Flighted on middle and leg, Rahane glances it to mid on.
Short and spinning in, Rahane gets on his back foot and punches it to point.
Floated on off, Rahane strokes it towards point and gets to the other end to score his first run of the session.
Short around off, Kohli cuts it but finds the man at point.
No ball from a spinner. Not a good sign. Muthusamy oversteps. He darts one on the pads, Kohli flicks it to the on side and eases to the other end.
Floated on off, Ajinkya blocks it.
On off, Ajinkya defends it to get through the over.
Good length ball on off, Virat blocks it.

FOUR! Gorgeous! Don't know what Kohli ate for lunch because from yesterday all he is eating is runs in this Test. Fuller on off, Kohli gets on his front foot and plays a wonderful cover drive. Bavuma dives and takes the pace off the ball  but Kohli hit it with such power that the ball still managed to beat the fielder to the fence.
Back of a length, VK blocks it off the back foot.
On off, defended by Kohli.
Another good looking cover drive but this is straight to the man.
On the pads, Virat glances it through square leg and takes a single. Rahane asks for the second as there is an overthrow but Kohli says no.
Maharaj starts with a flighted ball on middle and leg, Kohli defends it towards cover-point and gets a single.

OUT! Caught! Finally some success for South Africa on the day. Maharaj has found a way to get past the defense of Ajinkya Rahane. Keshav gives this air on off, the ball turns and bounces away from Rahane. He looks to defend but the ball kisses the outside edge of the bat and goes straight into the mitts of de Kock. The South African players appeal and the umpire after a slight delay raises his finger. This has been a tough tour for Keshav Maharaj but this might act as a sweetener as Rahane becomes his 100th Test  victim.
Jadeja is off the mark straightaway. Flighted on middle, Ravindra strokes it towards mid on and gets a single.
Floated on off, Kohli drives it to cover.
On the pads, Kohli stretches forward and takes it as a full toss. He glances it through square leg and takes three as the ball does not have the legs to reach the fence.
Floated on off, Jadeja blocks it.
Good length ball on off, Kohli drives it on the up to cover.

Just short! Good length ball outside off, it comes back in off the surface. Kohli initially looks to play but then decides to leave. The ball takes the edge of the bat and goes to the right of de Kock on the bounce. Quinton takes it with his right hand. Faf goes forward thinking it has carried but de Kock does not celebrate at all.
On the pads, Virat glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Length ball on off, Jadeja blocks it off the front foot.
Jadeja defends it from within the crease.
Length delivery outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Short outside off, it stays low a bit. Virat whips it to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Kohli strokes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Virat defends it with authority.
Short around off, Kohli punches it to the left of mid-wicket.

Oh! Good back up from Jadeja. Tossed up on off, Virat drives it straight to the right of Maharaj. Keshav dives and gets his hand to the ball. The ball deflects onto the stumps but Jadeja at the non-striker's end was inside his crease so he is safe.
Flighted on off, Virat pushes it to cover.
Length delivery way outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.

Short of a length delivery outside off, Jadeja cuts this one towards gully. Markram dives to his left to stop the ball and he parries it. Kohli spots the opportunity to snatch a single and the batters complete it comfortably.
Length delivery just outside off, it pitches and nips away. Kohli goes after it but the ball whizzes past his outside edge. Lucky for him he does not connect.
Kohli drives this one beautifully towards mid on but Rabada there stops it.

Length ball just outside off, Kohli looks to flick it towards the leg side but misses it. The ball goes off his thigh pad towards de Kock. The South African players think that there is some bat on it. They appeal but the umpire is unmoved and they decide against taking the review. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows no bat on that. Ball Tracker comes in to show that it was clipping the off pole so would not have mattered had they taken the review.
Pitched full and outside off, Jadeja makes the leave.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Jadeja pushes this floated delivery  towards mid on for a single.
Again floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on by Kohli.
Kohli prods forward and defends this one.
Length ball just outside off, Kohli does well to push it towards the point region.

Bad fielding overall by South Africa. Length ball on middle and off, Jadeja pushes it back towards the bowler. Rabada collects it and throws it towards de Kock but he is late in reacting to collect it as he didn't expect the throw. The batters snatch a single and both de Kock and Rabada are angry with each other.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Down the leg side, Kohli flicks it off his pads towards mid-wicket for a boundary. Nonchalant!
Short of a length ball outside off, Kohli pulls this one towards fine leg for a single.
Jadeja is completely bamboozled by this length delivery bowled by Rabada as the ball goes between his body and his bat as Ravindra looks to defend.
Length ball on middle and off, defends this one off the back foot.
Excellent running! Shorter on off, Kohli turns it behind square on the leg side and looks for two straightaway. Jadeja is quick too and they get it with ease.
Floated on off, Kohli plays it late towards short third man.
Tossed up on off, Virat plants his front foot forward and blocks it.
Flighted outside off, Virat drives it but straight to cover.

Poor from Vernon Philander. Flighted on middle, Kohli whips it to the right of mid on. Vernon Philander at mid on moves to that side but misfields allowing them to get two runs. Tiredness starting to show in South Africa's fielding now.
On off, Kohli nudges it towards cover and keeps the strike.
Back of a length ball on off, Kohli pulls it wide of short mid-wicket and gets a couple as Vernon Philander cleans it up coming from mid on.
Outside off on a length, Kohli leaves it alone.

FOUR! Delightful! Fuller ball around off, Kohli gets on his front foot and caresses it through covers with absolute class for a boundary. Jeez, you could watch this shot on loop and you will always admire it.
Fuller on off, Kohli this time just eases it to cover.
Oh! Length ball outside off, it comes back in. Kohli has a poke at it but gets beaten.
Length delivery on off, Kohli pushes it off his back foot and takes a single.
Flighted on off, Kohli pushes it to cover.

EDGED AND FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Kohli looks to play the cut with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes well wide of Faf du Plessis at first slip. The South African skipper is a bit late to react even though the ball was well wide of him.
Shorter on off, Virat punches it to cover.
On the pads, Kohli flicks it to square leg.
Tossed up on middle, Virat strokes it to mid on.

EDGED AND FOUR AGAIN! Kohli gets to his 150 with a bit of luck! Flighted on off, Kohli looks to drive it on the up. The ball turns and finds the outside edge of Kohli's willow. It goes to the right of Faf du Plessis at first slip. He is late to react once again and the ball races away to the fence. Things starting to happen for the left-arm spinner. Subdued celebration from the Indian skipper. Looks like he is eyeing a double ton.
Length ball on off, Jadeja dabs it to gully.
On the pads, Jadeja turns it down to square leg for one.
Good length ball on off, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on off, VK pushes it to mid off.

Good length ball on off, Kohli taps it to the off side on side of the pitch and calls for a quick single. Bavuma comes running in from short cover, gets to the ball and hits the stumps at the non-striker's end with a dive. Jadeja though was well in.
Length ball on off, Ravindra keeps it out.
Shorter around off, Kohli cuts it to point.
Flighted delivery on off, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
EDGED AND FOUR! Flighted on off, Kohli looks to drive but once again he ends up edging it. The ball goes wide of first slip and races away to the fence.
Floated on off, Kohli pushes it back towards the bowler.
Shorter on off, Kohli plays it to the man at short third man.
Flighted on off, Kohli strokes it to mid off.
Length ball on middle and leg, it comes in just a bit off the surface. Jadeja looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Good length ball on off, Jadeja taps it towards point and comes out for a single but Kohli sends him back. Umpire Chris Gaffaney gives Jadeja his first official warning as Jadeja was running from the danger area.
Length ball on off, RJ defends it.
Bouncer! A very well directed short ball. It is around the body, Jadeja ducks under it. Anrich Nortje has a stare at Jadeja and Ravindra gives him back too.
Length delivery on off, Jadeja blocks it off the back foot.
On the pads, Jadeja looks to leave it alone and the ball hits his pad and goes to the fine leg fence. No run will be counted as Jadeja was not offering any shot.
Tossed up on off, Kohli pushes it towards point for one.
The batsman has driven it straight down the ground.

Funny! Floated around off, Jadeja looks to defend but the ball spins in and lobs up off his pad. The ball goes behind de Kock. Quinton runs to his right and in an attempt to turn slips and falls in the process.
Shorter on off, Jadeja defends it off the back foot.
On the pads, Jadeja pads it away.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball on off, Kohli strokes it to point.
Good length ball on off, Virat pushes it towards cover.
Full and on the off pole line, pushed towards the man at cover.
FOUR! Bouncer down the leg side, Kohli just helps it along towards the fine leg fence. The man in the deep cannot stop it inside the ropes.
On the pads of Kohli, he flicks it towards square leg for a couple.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards the man at short cover.
Floated just outside off, Jadeja pushes this one towards cover and takes a single.
Shortish ball outside off, Kohli cuts this one towards cover-point and takes a couple.
Kohli prods forward and defends this off the front foot.
Kohli pushes this one towards cover and takes a single to bring up the 50-run stand between Jadeja and Kohli. It has come in good time as India look to increase their run rate.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads of Jadeja, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja blocks it.
Length ball outside off, Jadeja knows where his off pole is and leaves it alone.
On middle and off, Jadeja glances it to square leg and shouts a  loud no to his skipper.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off and middle, Jadeja looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
Floated around off, Kohli defends it towards cover-point.
Short around off, Kohli cuts it wide of point and gets a single.
Floated outside off, Ravindra leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle, RJ pushes it back to the bowler.
On the stumps, Jadeja keeps it out.
On the pads, Jadeja turns it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Fuller on off and middle, Kohli drives it through covers, wide of sweeper cover for two.
Length delivery on off, Kohli defends it towards cover.
Length delivery on off, Kohli defends it with soft hands towards cover and gets a single.
Outside off, Jadeja offers a very good leave.
Back of a length ball on off. Jadeja taps it towards backward point and comes down for a single. Kohli says 'no'. Ravindra comes down but realises he was on the danger end so he hops away.
Short on off, RJ blocks it.
Flighted on off, Kohli runs it down to point.
On middle, Kohli strokes it towards mid on for a run.
FOUR! Easy picking! Full toss on off, Jadeja slams it through long off for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Jadeja. Shorter on middle and off, Jadeja whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Once again on the pads, Jadeja glances it to the on side for one.
The batsman has driven it through mid-off. One run added to the total.
FOUR! Beautiful shot by Kohli this, full ball on middle and off, Kohli smashes this past Philander for a boundary through mid on.
Kohli has driven this full ball superbly through the cover region but he gets just a single off it.
