Length ball on off, Jadeja pushes this one towards point and takes a single.
On the pads of Kohli, he flicks this one through mid-wicket for a couple.
Kohli drives this one towards the mid off fielder.
Great running this by Kohli! He flicks this one towards mid-wicket and takes off, Jadeja responds and the batters take one.
Floated on middle, Kohli works this one towards the leg side.
Superb fielding by Faf du Plessis at first slip. Kohli rocks onto the back foot and tries to guide it towards third man. Faf dives low to his right and parries it straight towards de Kock.
FOUR! Short of a length ball and punished by Kohli! He rocks back in his crease and pulls this one through mid-wicket for a boundary.
The batsman has driven it straight down the ground.
FOUR! Another similar delivery and again given the treatment by Kohli! Back of a length, Kohli rocks back and slams it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Kohli punches the last ball of the over towards point and takes a single. He is just 11 short of 200 runs and Kohli will be looking to get there before the end of this session.
Philander bowls this around off on a good length, Kohli taps it towards point and changes end.
Quick single! Nicely done! A slightly fullish length, Jadeja pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
On the fourth stump line, pushed back to the bowler.
Fullish ball just outside off, Kohli pushes this one towards short extra cover for a single.
Going down the leg side, Jadeja looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Good length ball just outside off, Jadeja pushes this one towards point where the fielder does well to gather it.
Full toss on the pads, flicked in front of square leg for a single by Kohli.
Flatter on middle and off, Jadeja blocks it out.
On the pads, Jadeja tucks this one towards the leg side.
Floated on middle and leg, Jadeja pushes this one towards mid on for a single.
This time Kohli pushes it towards mid on for a single.
On the pads, Jadeja flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery on off, Kohli blocks it towards the off side.
On the pads, pushed towards long on for a single.
Short and outside off, Jadeja cuts it towards backward point for a couple.
A touch short again, Jadeja this time pushes this one towards cover-point for a couple. A bit of yes and no between Jadeja and Kohli for the third but in the end they decide against it.
On the pads, Jadeja flicks it away but straight to the man at square leg.
Jadeja defends this one by presenting the full face of the bat. AND THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Floated on middle, Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.
First run of the final session. Shorter on the pads, Kohli whips it towards mid-wicket for one.
Darted on the pads, Jadeja flicks it towards square leg for one.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Another one which is short and on the pads, Kohli turns it towards deep mid-wicket for one. This brings up the 100-run stand between the two.
Short on off, Jadeja pulls it but to the man at deep mid-wicket.
Flighted on the stumps, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Record making run! On the pads, Kohli whips it to the on side and gets a single. With that single, Kohli goes past Sir Don Bradman's tally of 6996 runs in Tests.
On the stumps, Jadeja defends it.
Once again Jadeja calmly blocks it.
On the pads, turned away to square leg.
Short on off, Jadeja punches it towards covers for a couple.
On the pads, Kohli turns it to the on side and gets an easy single.
Flighted on off, Jadeja defends it with soft hands towards cover and gives the strike to Kohli who is on 198.
Shorter on off, Kohli punches it back to the bowler.

DOUBLE HUNDRED FOR VIRAT KOHLI! His 7th Test double ton. This man is just pure class. All the adjectives in the world is just not enough to describe this man. On the pads, Kohli turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a couple to get to his double hundred. He raises his bat with a huge smile on his face. His teammates and the crowd stand up to applaud the King! The King is back! This has not been his best year in Test according to his 'out of the world' standards but boy doesn't he make his bat do all the talking?
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Darted on the pads, Kohli flicks it to square leg.
Shorter on off, Jadeja punches it to the off side.
Flighted on off, Jadeja pushes it to long off for a single.
Shorter on off, Kohli punches it to the off side for one.
Flicked to the on side for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Kohli lofts it over mid on towards long on for a single.
Another single which is milked down to long on.
Floated on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short delivery outside off, Jadeja cuts this one towards cover-point for a single.
SIX! Bad ball and taken full toll off it! Short of a length ball on middle and leg, Kohli rocks back and slams this one over mid-wicket for a biggie!
No ball! Muthusamy oversteps! The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Kohli opens the face of his bat and guides it towards third man.

No ball! What has Muthusamy done here! It looked to everyone like he had got the wicket of Virat Kohli twice in two Tests but MUTHUSAMY HAS OVERSTEPPED! This is criminal from him, especially being a spinner. The ball is floated just outside off, Kohli prods forward and looks to defend but edges it. Faf du Plessis at first slip takes a very good low catch. Kohli starts walking off the pitch but the umpire wants to check the No Ball and he stops Kohli. He goes to the third umpire and the replays show that Muthusamy has indeed overstepped.
Full and floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on for a single.
FOUR! Jadeja puts his foot down on the paddle now. He drives this full and floated one through the cover region for a majestic boundary.
Short around off, Kohli looks to cut but gets a bottom edge which goes to the keeper on the bounce.
On the pads, Kohli flicks it to the on side  and gets a single.
Floated on middle, Jadeja strokes it to long on for one.
In the air but safe. Flighted on off, Kohli looks to go over covers but gets no timing on it. Luckily it falls short of the man in the deep so just a single.
Milked to long on for one.
Short on off, Kohli punches it to cover.
FOUR! Short of a length delivery on off, Jadeja rocks back and pulls this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Another short delivery punished by Jadeja! Shorter and outside off, Jadeja pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for another boundary.
Jadeja cuts this shorter one outside off in front of point and gets a couple of runs.
Another shorter delivery outside off, Jadeja pushes this off the back foot towards covers for a couple. This brings up the 12th fifty for Ravindra Jadeja and he brings out his trademark celebration.
Jadeja opens the face of his bat and guides this one towards third man for a single.
Kohli gets on the back foot and defends it. End of a very expensive over, 13 runs off it.
FOUR! Powerful shot! Floated on middle and leg, Jadeja lifts this one over the bowler's head and the ball goes into the long on fence for a boundary.
Short delivery outside off, Jadeja looks to cut it but is beaten by the bounce on it.
Floated outside off, Jadeja lofts it inside out over the cover fielder for a single.
Kohli punches this short ball towards long on for a single.
Jadeja pushes this one towards point and takes a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! How lucky can Kohli be? Shorter and outside off, Kohli tries to cut it but the ball goes off the inside edge towards the left of Faf du Plessis. However, he has already shifted his body-weight towards the right side and cannot hold onto it. The ball races to the third man fence for a boundary.
SIX! Jadeja goes downtown! Tossed up on off, Jadeja comes down the track and whacks it over the bowler's head for a handsome biggie.
Maharaj goes short, Ravindra pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! Kohli too now takes the aerial route! Floated on off, Virat comes down the track and smashes it over long off for a biggie.
Short again, Kohli finds the fielder at mid-wicket with his pull.
FOUR! Typical Kohli whip here. Floated on the pads, Kohli uses his wrists and whips it through mid on for a boundary.

FOUR! Now on the off side. Disastrous return for Maharaj. 21 runs of the over. Short outside off, Kohli cuts it with sheer venom and gets a boundary. That also takes Virat Kohli's international run count to 21,000. India have cut loose here and are in T20 mode now.
FOUR! Short ball wide outside off, Jadeja rocks back in his crease and cuts it towards the cover-point region for a boundary.
Wide outside off, Jadeja guides this one towards third man for a single.
Kohli pushes this off the back foot towards long on for a single.
SIX! Jadeja now dances down the track and slams this one over the bowler's head for a flat maximum. Powerful hitting this!
Off the back foot, Jadeja cuts this towards point.
Jadeja pushes this one off the back foot towards cover for a single.
Short of a length ball outside off, Jadeja cuts this one towards cover-point for a single.
Kohli pushes this one towards the man at point.

Shortish on middle and leg, Kohli punches this one towards long on for a single. Maharaj dives to his right in an attempt to save the single but the ball goes past him. He might have hurt himself in the process too.

Great running! Commendable fitness of the Indian batters this! Down the leg side this one, Jadeja tickles it down the leg side. Kohli is still fresh like he is batting on 32 not 232 and he completes the third run easily.
Another couple! This time Kohli opens the face of the bat and helps it to third man. The batters take two off it.
Kohli punches this one off the back foot towards cover for a single.
Floated on off, Kohli defends it towards cover-point.
Short on top of middle, Kohli gets on his back foot and punches it wide of mid on but gets no runs for it.
Short outside off, Kohli cuts it towards point for a single. 100 comes up for the session.
Flighted on off, Jadeja slams it to long off for one.
On the pads, Kohli tickles it fine down the leg side. Faf du Plessis gives it a chase and saves it before the ropes. The batsmen come back for the third. 200-run stand comes up between the two.
Flighted on off, Jaddu keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Kohli milks it to long on and eases to the other end.
FOUR! It goes with double the pace that came in. Elgar bowls it slower and flight it on off, Jadeja smashes it over the bowler's head. The ball bounces inside the ropes and goes away for a boundary.
Short around off, Jaddu cuts it towards deep point for one.

Straighter one outside off, Kohli looks to cut but misses. The ball just about misses the edge. Elgar goes up in confidence but nothing from the umpire. Kohli and de Kock look at Elgar and both of them have a huge smile on their faces.
Tosssed up on off, VK pushes it to mid off.
Shorter around off, Kohli late cuts it towards third man and keeps the strike.
Floated on middle and leg, Kohli milks it to long on for one.
Short and wide outside off, Jadeja cuts it to deep point and walks to the other end.
That has spun off the rough! Flighted outside off, Kohli looks to drive but misses. The ball spins away and beats de Kock as well. Du Plessis at first slip dives to left and saves runs for his side.
FOUR! Demolished! Shorter on off, Kohli gets on his back foot and hammers his pull through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short around off, Kohli punches it off the back foot towards cover for one.
Jadeja strokes it to deep point and keeps the strike.
On the pads, Jadeja flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Short from Elgar, Jadeja pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Around off and short, Kohli dabs it down towards third man for a single.
Flighted on off, Jadeja comes down the track and nudges it to long off for a run.

FOUR! Kohli brings his 250 in style. I am out of words. The only thing I can talk abiut Kohli is, he has been batting for so long but has not broken a sweat. Top-class fitness! Floated on middle, Kohli whacks it over mid-wicket for a boundary to achieve this feat.
Tossed up on off, Kohli pushes it towards cover for a single. 600 comes up for India.
Flatter outside off, Kohli looks to flat bat it through covers but this one comes off the lower half of his bat. Just a single.
Tossed up on off, Jadeja defends it to the on side.

OUT! Jadeja holes out and with that India have decided to declare! And guess what? Muthusamy has not overstepped this time. Tossed up on middle, Jadeja looks to whack it over long off. He gets the height but not the distance. It goes to the right of long off, Theunis de Bruyn runs to his right and takes a very good catch. Jadeja misses out on a well-deserved ton but this shows the heart of this man. He could have taken his time to achieve the milestone but he decides to go for the big one and falls. Nonetheless, the man has played an innings worth being called as 'Sir'. India declare on  601/5.
Ishant Sharma starts with a length ball just outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
This time on middle, Elgar defends this off the back foot onto the pitch.
Back of a length ball outside off, Dean leaves it alone.

Loose shot this by Elgar and this is not what South Africa want. Full length ball outside off, Elgar goes for a drive towards cover but thick edges it uppishly towards point. Luckily for him there is no fielder there and the ball rolls towards deep point where Jadeja mops it up. Two runs taken.
Length ball on off, Elgar lets the ball go.
Good length ball on middle and off, Elgar pushes it back towards Ishant.
Length ball outside off, Markram lets it go.

OUT! LBW! What a comeback into the squad by Umesh Yadav! He has taken the wicket of Aiden Markram on just his second ball and South Africa have already lost their first wicket. Bowls a good length delivery just outside off, the last ball nipped away, this one kept on going straight and beat the inside edge of Markram's bat. The Indian players go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Markram does not review it and that is a good decision as the Ball Tracker later on rolls and shows three reds and it is a good decision that they opted against taking the review.
Good length ball on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.
De Bruyn comes onto the front foot and defends it with the full face of the bat.
Fullish delivery outside off, de Bruyn is late in bringing down his bat and inside edges it onto the pads.
Full again, de Bruyn pushes this one towards mid on. Shubman Gill, the substitute fielder there misfields and the ball rolls towards long on which allows the batters to take two.
Full ball on off, Elgar drives it down the ground.
Another fuller ball on middle and off, Elgar pushes it back to the bowler.
Sharma bowls this one on a length, Elgar gets onto the back foot and defends it.
Good length delivery on middle and off, pushed towards mid off.
Length ball on middle and off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR! First boundary of the innings and it is off the bat of Dean Elgar. Down the leg side, Elgar flicks it fine down the leg side and the ball races to the fence.
Length ball on off, de Bruyn shoulders arms to let that one through.
FOUR! Superb shot this! Length delivery just outside off, de Bruyn gets on his back foot and punches this through the cover region for a boundary.
Woah! That has stayed very low! Too low! Full ball just outside off, de Bruyn looks to play at it but the ball stays extremely low. It goes to the keeper after a couple of bounces. Weird stuff.
De Bruyn has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery. The batsmen have run through for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Chopped on by Elgar and it looks like South Africa are going to collapse here. Length ball just outside off, Elgar is caught in two minds whether to play at it or not. Initially he looks to play at it but then tries to leave it alone. It is too late by then as the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads and then hits the stumps. Dean looks distraught at how his wicket has fallen but the Indians are ecstatic.
On the pads, Bavuma works it towards the leg side for a single. Bavuma is off the mark.
FOUR! Beautiful! Overpitched on off, Bavuma gets on his front foot and plays a delightful drive through covers for a boundary.
Bavuma follows it up with a calm defense.
Length ball outside off, Temba leaves it alone.
Full and swinging in, Bavuma plays it nicely wide of mid on and gets a couple as Shami goes behind it and mops it up.

NOT OUT! Bump ball it is! Very full on the pads, Bavuma looks to flick but the ball hits the toe end of the bat and goes fine down the leg side. Saha dives to his left, stretches to his left and gathers a fine take. The umpires have a word and then take it upstairs with the soft signal as OUT. Replay rolls in and shows that the ball had hit the bottom edge of his bat and bumped on its way to the keeper. Nonetheless a fine take from Saha.
Good length ball on off, Bavuma blocks it.
Umesh hits the deck hard on off, de Bruyn blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! This should give Theunis some much needed confidence. On the pads, de Bruyn flicks it uppishly through the vacant mid-wicket region for a boundary.
FOUR! This is even better from de Bruyn! Fuller around off, Theunis gets on his front foot and strokes it through point for a boundary.
After two consecutive boundaries, Theunis calmly defends this one with a straight bat.
Outside off, de Bruyn is in no mood to play at that.
Another one on the fourth stump line, Theunis leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Bavuma defends it with soft hands towards cover and gets a quick single.
Full down the leg side, Theunis looks to flick but misses. Saha stretches to his left and does well to take it.
Nicely blocked! Fuller on middle, Theunis defends it with authority towards mid on.
FOUR! Gorgeous! Fuller on off, de Bruyn gets on his front foot and drives it with class through mid off for a boundary. De Bruyn looks in the mood.
Theunis follows a lovely boundary with a sensible front foot defense.
On off, de Bruyn pushes it to mid off.
On the fourth stump line, Temba leaves it alone.
Fuller around off, Bavuma defends it towards point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
EDGED BUT JUST SHORT! Good length ball around off, it angles away a bit. Bavuma looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. It falls short of Virat Kohli who dives to his right at third slip.
On off, Bavuma pushes it to point.
Length ball on off, Bavuma looks to play it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Jadeja starts with a flighted delivery on off, de Bruyn defends it off the front foot.
The batsman gets a leading edge on that one. However it falls safe and no harm done.
In the air but in no man's land. Flighted on off, Theunis looks to flick but gets a leading edge. Luckily it falls wide of long on.
Floated on off, Theunis leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, de Bruyn blocks it.
EDGED AND JUST SHORT. Tossed  up outside off, Theunis looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. Rahane at first slip, comes forward and looks to take it but he gets it just on the bounce.

OUT! Caught! Shami strikes on his very first ball. What a start this is for Shami. Brilliant review too by Virat Kohli. He cannot do anything wrong today, can he? Shami comes steaming in and hits the deck hard around the channel just outside off. Bavuma looks to punch it on the up. The ball goes behind to the keeper who takes it. The Indian players put in a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli signals the 'T' and takes it upstairs. Ultra Edge rolls in and shows a spike on it as the ball goes past the bat. Bavuma has to walk back and South Africa in deep trouble now.

Huge appeal but turned down by the umpire. Looked to be missing leg. Full and pacy ball on middle and leg, Nortje looks to defend but the ball hits him flush on the pads. There is a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. India don't take the review as they too think it is going down leg.
Bouncer! Nortje ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Anrich defends it off the back foot.

Excellent review from Anrich Nortje. Excellent delivery from Shami. Back of a length ball on off, the ball rises onto the batsman. Nortje looks to defend but the ball hits something on its way to the keeper. The Indian players go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Nortje takes the review straightaway. It shows it was kissing his arm on its way to the keeper. Kohli knew it and hence he was not up in celebration earlier. The night watchman survives but one cannot say for how long.
Full on off, Nortje pushes it towards point.
Tossed up on the pads, de Bruyn looks to flick but gets an inside edge on it.
Flighted on off, de Bruyn keeps it out.
On the stumps, de Bruyn lunges forward and defends it.
Theunis gets on the front foot and calmly defends this one.
Outside off, Theunis leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, TdB has nothing to do with it.
Back of a length ball on off, Nortje looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and pacy on middle and off, Nortje looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Shami should have had his second. Mayank Agarwal is the culprit here. Good length ball on middle and off. Nortje looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards fourth slip. Mayank Agarwal there reacts late and hence goes with just one hand, his right hand. The ball lobs of his hand and goes behind. They take a single.
On the pads, de Bruyn flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Jaffa! Shami hits the deck hard around off, Nortje looks to defend but the ball zips away and goes past the outside edge.
Very full on off, Nortje does well to get his bat down and negotiate it.
Flighted on the stumps, Theunis defends it.
Gives this air on off, de Bruyn keeps it out.
Slightly shorter on off and middle, Bruyn defends it.
Shorter on off, Theunis punches it off the back foot.
On the stumps, TdB keeps it out.
Floated around off, Thenuis lunges forward and blocks it.
Good length ball on off, Nortje defends it by getting right behind the ball.
Bouncer around the body. Anrich ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, Nortje leaves it alone. The ball swings in late after it goes past the stump.
Another one that swings past the stumps. Length ball outside off, Nortje leaves it alone. The ball raises and swings in after the stumps. Credit to Saha who does well to gather it.
Full on off, Nortje keeps it out.
Full on off, Nortje turns it behind square on the leg side and gets to the other end. He will keep the strike. That is a risky move.
Tossed up on off and middle, Nortje defends it to the on side.
Shorter on off, Anrich blocks it.
On off, Nortje bends his back and defends it.
Floated outside off, Nortje leaves it alone.
This one is tossed up on off, AN does well to block it.
Tossed up on off, Nortje comes down the track and looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge towards the fielder at point. And that will be STUMPS ON DAY 2.

Beauty to start the day. Shami steams in and bowls a full length ball outside off, it comes in after pitching. Theunis shows his awarness regarding his off stump and the ball goes just outside off stump. Good ball but also a good leave.
Bowls on the fourth stump line. Theunis leaves this alone as well. The ball jags back in after it goes past the stump. Good carry to the keeper as it goes to Saha.

FOUR! Beautiful shot to get the first runs of the day. First ball which is on the stumps. It is on middle and leg, de Bruyn uses his wrists and flicks it between mid on and mid-wicket for a glorious boundary.
Length ball on off, Theunis defends it off the front foot.
Goes back to bowling on the fourth stump line. Theunis does not disturb that.
Length ball outside off, de Bruyn lets it carry to the keeper. No swing on the last ball. 4 runs off the first over of the day.
Umesh starts with a good length ball on off. Unlike Shami, Umesh does not get any swing first up. Nortje defends it off the front foot.
Nice ball! Length ball on middle and leg, it is pacy and comes in with the angle. Nortje looks to drive but the ball hits him on the pads.

Edged and goes on the bounce. Length delivery on off, this one shapes away. Nortje looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. He plays it with soft hand and hence the ball goes to the man at gully on a bounce.
Nortje gets his first run of the day. On the pads, Anrich turns it to fine leg and gets a single.
Full on off, it comes in after pitching. Theunis plays it with the angle and pushes it to the left of mid on.
Similar to the previous one. Full and angling in. De Bruyn pushes it to Ashwin at mid on.
Bouncer! First effort ball of the day. It is on off and middle. Anrich keeps his eyes on the ball and sways away from it.

OUT! Caught! The night watchman goes early in the morning. Back of a length ball closer to the body, Anrich looks to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to the right of fourth slip. Indian captain, Virat Kohli there dives to that side and takes a good low catch. He cannot do anything wrong in this game, can he? South Africa lose their first wicket on Day 3. India strike early and Shami gets his second of the game.

BOTTOM EDGE AND FOUR! Faf du Plessis gets off the mark in a lucky way. Excellent ball by Shami. He steams in and hits the deck hard around off, Faf looks to play but then decides to leave. The ball comes back in sharply. Faf is late in getting his bat away. The ball takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps to the fine leg region for a boundary. Sometime the game is cruel on the bowlers and this is one such occasion.
Length delivery on off, Faf defends it right off the middle of his bat.
Outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.

Fuller outside off, it shapes in after pitching. Faf offers a confident leave to get through the over. End of a brilliant over from Shami. 4 runs and a wicket from the over. That boundary too came in a streaky way.
Length delivery on off, Theunis defends it off the front foot.
Away from the off stump, Theunis does not go chasing after it.
FOUR! Easy! Slightly overpitched on off, Theunis just times his push through extra cover. Ishant Sharma goes behind it with no motivation to stop it and the ball eases away to the fence.
De Bruyn smartly follows the boundary with a calm front foot defense.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Length ball around off, de Bruyn punches it cleanly off his back foot but straight to the man at cover.
Outside off, De Bruyn shoulders arms to this one.
BEAUTY! Shami is bowling some real gems here. Good length ball outside off, the balls venomously comes back in. Faf offers a dangerous leave and the ball just about goes over the stumps.
On the pads, Faf glances it to the on side and gets a couple.
Way outside off, this is an easy leave for du Plessis.
Slightly shorter around off, Faf defends it off his back foot and shouts a loud no to his partner.
This one shapes away. Good length ball outside off, Faf shoulders arms to it. The ball moves away once it goes past the stumps.
On top of off, Faf defends it to get through the over.
Nice punch. Length ball around off, Theunis gets on his back foot and punches it through covers for a couple. He is looking very good against the pacers. Moves to 30 with that.
Fuller on off, de Bruyn defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, De Bruyn blocks it
Around off, Theunis pushes it to cover.
On a length, de Bruyn defends it with a straight bat.

OUT! Cuaght! Excellent catch from Saha! Umesh strikes and the man who was looking very good departs. South Africa have half their side back in the pavilion. Brilliant ball from Umesh. He hits the deck hard around off, it is in the channel of uncertainty. The ball moves away off the deck. Theunis looks to punch it on the up but the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to the right of Saha. He dives on that side and takes a superb catch. India are all over South Africa. Forget the spinners, the pacers are troubling the Proteas.
On the pads, du Plessis glances it to the on side.
Outside off, du Plessis leaves it.
Another one away from the stumps and du Plessis does not disturb that.
Full on off, Faf keeps it out.
Good length ball on off, Faf keeps it out.
Full on off, du Plessis gets behind it and defends it to the off side.

Uppish but safe! Fuller on off, the ball sticks on the surface as it comes to de Kock. Quinton looks to defend but he checks his shot. He ends up hitting it uppishly. Luckily for South Africa it is away from the fielder at cover.
FOUR! Gorgeous! This is right off the meat! Full on off, de Kock this time commits himself to the drive and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Slightly pulls his length back, de Kock pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, de Kock leaves it alone.
Around middle and leg, de Kock blocks it to the on side.
Fuller on off, de Kock defends it right of the middle to the off side.
Ishant starts with a length ball outside off, Faf shoulders arms to it. No swing first up for the tall bowler.
Full and pitching on off and middle, this one comes in with the angle. Du Plessis glances it towards fine leg for a single.
First good ball from Sharma in the morning. Fuller ball outside off, it zips away off the deck. De Kock goes chasing after it and the ball just about beats his outside edge on its way to the keeper.
Good length ball pitching on off, it goes away with the angle. Quinton does not trouble this time.
Goes back to bowling full. It is on off, de Kock pushes it to mid off.
On top of middle, de Kock tucks it to square leg. Just a run off Ishant's first.
Floated on off, Faf defends it. No spin for Ash first up.
Tossed up on off, du Plessis blocks it off the front foot.
Darts one on middle and leg, du Plessis turns it to the on side.
Flighted on off, Faf keeps it out.
Floated outside off, du Plessis looks to play the sweep but misses. The ball hits him on the pads. There is excitement from the Indian players.
On the pads, du Plessis flicks it to the on side.
Length ball on off, de Kock pushes it to cover for one.
FOUR! Good timing! Full around off, Faf plants his front foot out and drives it through point with brilliant timing for a boundary.
Back of a length ball around off, du Plessis defends it off his back foot.
Fuller on off, du Plessis pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Faf leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball on off, Faf looks to defend it with soft hands. The ball takes an outside edge and goes all along the ground through the vacant third slip region for a boundary. Rohit Sharma at second slip dives but had no chance stopping that.
Come around the wicket and tosses it up on off, de Kock keeps it out.
Floated on off, Quinton defends it onto the ground.
FOUR! Nicely played! Floated on middle and off, Quinton creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Shorter on off, de Kock gets on his back foot and defends it.
Driven towards the mid off region.
Gives this one air around off, de Kock looks to defend but keeps it out off the outer half of his bat. It goes wide of the man at silly point.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by du Plessis.
Good length ball on the off pole line, du Plessis pushes it back towards mid on.
On the hips of du Plessis, he tucks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Length ball outside off by Sharma, de Kock leaves it alone.
After a hiccup, Ishant bowls another length ball outside off which de Kock shoulders arms to.
On the off pole line, de Kock guides this one towards the man at gully.
Floated outside off, du Plessis looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards third man for a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! De Kock thick edges this floated one outside off, it flies wide of the first slip fielder and goes towards the third man fence for a boundary. Streaky! Had there been a second slip or gully fielder in place, it would have gone straight to him. With such a mammoth score on the board, India can afford to take that risk.
Floated on middle and off, pushed towards mid off.
On middle and off again, de Kock blocks this out.
Tossed up on off, pushed towards the cover region.
On the pads of de Kock, he flicks it towards mid-wicket. No runs taken.
Shami bowls this one outside off, du Plessis pushes this one towards cover and takes three while the fielder mops it up in the deep.
On the pads of de Kock, he flicks this one towards mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Length ball outside off, de Kock looks to cut it but the ball goes off the bottom edge towards Saha.
De Kock has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, de Kock opens the face of his bat and guides it towards the third man region for a boundary.
Shortish on middle and off, du Plessis blocks it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and floated, defended off the front foot.
Du Plessis defends this one from within the crease.
Down the leg side, du Plessis works it towards the leg side.

A huge appeal for LBW by the Indian team but the umpire is unmoved. Outside off, spinning back into the batsman, du Plessis tries to block but misses the ball. It hits him on the back pad and the Indian players appeal. The umpire denies it and India opt against the review. The replays show that it was going above the stumps. Good decision by the umpire.
Good length ball on middle and off, de Kock defends it off front foot.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball on middle and off, de Kock gets onto the back foot and defends it.
Full and on off, de Kock pushes it towards mid off.
Length ball on off, it goes towards the point region.
FOUR! Great shot on the up by de Kock! Good length ball on off, he drives it stylishly through the cover region for a boundary.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

SIX! Powerful shot over the bowler's head by du Plessis! Jadeja floats this one on middle and off, du Plessis gets on the front foot and smashes it down the ground for a maximum. First runs conceded by Jadeja in this innings.
Flatter on off, du Plessis blocks it out.
On middle and off, blocked out.
Du Plessis stays within the crease and blocks it out.
On the pads, du Plessis flicks it towards mid-wicket and retains strike.
Length ball outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, Faf does not bother to go after it.
Outside off, left alone by Faf.
Fuller on middle and leg, du Plessis looks to drive it towards mid on but it goes off the leading edge towards point.
FOUR! This time Faf connects well and the ball races away. On the pads, du Plessis flicks this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Down the leg side, du Plessis looks to flick but misses it. The ball goes on the bounce to the left of Saha where he dives and gathers it.

FOUR! Short and wide outside off, de Kock drives it through point for a fabulous boundary. The fielder there gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. 50-run stand up between de Kock and Faf du Plessis.
On the pads, de Kock flicks this one towards square leg and takes a single.
Full and floated on off, driven towards the mid off region for another single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
De Kock defends this one off the front foot.
On the pads, de Kock tucks this one towards mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Faf gets down on one knee and sweeps this one towards square leg for a single.
On the pads of de Kock, he flicks it behind square for a single.
FOUR! This time du Plessis gets the timing perfect! Floated on middle and off, Faf sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Du Plessis defends it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Du Plessis defends this one by staying back in his crease.
Du Plessis gets on the back foot and punches it towards long on for a single. Retains strike.
EDGED AND FOUR! Jadeja floats this one just outside off, it pitches and spins away. Faf looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past the second slip fielder for a boundary.
Defends this one off the front foot.
Du Plessis defends this one  by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Du Plessis defends this one off the back foot.
FOUR! Full and wide outside off, du Plessis drives this one through cover for a boundary. Beautiful drive!
FOUR! This time from the other side of the fielder at cover but the same result. It races to the fence at cover for another boundary.
Shortish outside off, de Kock leaves it alone.
De Kock defends this one off the back foot.
On the pads, de Kock flicks it towards square leg.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Full and floated on middle, de Kock drives this one through mid on for another boundary. A flurry of boundaries in the past few overs.

OUT! TIMBER! What a beauty by Ravichandran Ashwin! De Kock cannot believe he has been bowled and is still having a look at the stumps. Ashwin bowls a flatter delivery on middle and off, the ball pitches and spins away a touch. De Kock is in his crease looking to defend it off his back foot but the ball goes past his outside edge. It just about clips the bails of the off pole and the ball is gathered by Saha behind the stumps. De Kock is confused about what happened. His skipper asks him from the other end whether he nicked it to which de Kock denies. De Kock then asks one of the Indian players and he replies that de Kock has been bowled. He looks at the giant screen and then starts walking back to the pavilion. South Africa 6 down now and du Plessis looks like the lone warrior now.
Floated on off, du Plessis defends it towards point.
Shorter on off, Faf punches it towards cover.
Flighted on off, Faf defends it off the front foot.
Flatter on the stumps, Faf keeps it out.
Jaddu goes short. Faf keeps his calm and keeps it out.
Flighted around the stumps, Faf defends it to get through the over.
Beauty! Quicker one juts outside off, Muthusamy looks to defend but the ball misses the outside edge by just a whisker.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! Flighted on off, Senuran pushes it towards cover and goes for a quick single. Pujara gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the bowler's end. It is not a bad throw but bounces just in front of Ashwin. He misses it. Umesh Yadav backing up gets a bad bounce and it goes past him for a boundary.

Comical! On the pads, du Plessis turns it behind the square on the leg side. Muthusamy is adamant for a run and keeps on going even though Faf does not want the run. Du Plessis surrenders as Muthusamy is more than halfway down the track. He is baffled by Senuran's determination for the run.
Shorter around off, Muthusamy dabs it down to third man for one.
Flighted on off, Faf defends it off the front foot.

Virat thinks there was a noise but the rest feel there is not. Floated outside off, Faf looks to sweep but misses. The ball goes under his bat to the keeper. Virat asks his teammates and then decides not to go for the review.
Flatter one outside off spinning back in, Muthusamy pads it away.

DROPPED BY VIRAT KOHLI! Finally a moment when the Indian skipper does something wrong. A tough chance but you expect the Indian skipper to take that one. Floated on middle and off, Muthusamy looks to flick it towards the leg side. The ball goes uppishly to the right of short mid-wicket where Kohli is positioned. He dives and tries to pluck it out with one hand but the ball does not stick in his hand. Muthusamy breathes a sigh of relief because had he got out, the resistance after this looks pretty bleak.
Muthusamy has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Muthusamy watchfully keeps it out.
Outside off,, not coming back in enough. Muthusamy pads it away.
Senuran shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Du Plessis gets on the back foot and defends it out.
Fuller this time, pushed towards the leg side.
Fuller one on the pads, du Plessis pushes it towards long on for a single.
Ashwin darts this one into Muthusamy, he blocks it out well.
Muthusamy comes onto the front foot to block this one out but it comes off the inside edge onto the pads.

Jaffa by Ashwin to end the session. Gives this one a lot of air, Muthusamy looks to defend this one off the front foot but the ball pitches and turns away sharply beating the outside edge of Muthusamy's blade. Oohs and Aahs all around but Muthusamy survives. LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Run straightaway post the Lunch session. Jadeja starts with a very full delivery on middle, Faf milk sit to long off and gets a single.
Tossed up outside off, Muthusamy pads it away.

Floated very full on off and middle. Almost a yorker. Senuran looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads behind the stumps to the on side where Rahane from leg slip collects the ball.
Tossed up on off, Muthusamy calmly blocks it.
Flatter on off, Muthusamy defends it off the front foot.
Quicker on off, Muthusamy looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated on off, du Plessis gets on his front foot and blocks it.
Gives this one air on off, Faf pushes it to mid off.
On the stumps, Faf keeps it out.
Tosses it up on off, Faf defends it.
Loopy ball around off, du Plessis sweeps it towards square leg for a single.
Darted on the pads, Faf glances it towards mid-wicket and keeps the strike.
Flighted on off and middle, Muthusamy blocks it.

OUT! LBW! Brilliant decision from umpire Nigel Llong! India strike very soon after the break. Floated delivery outside off, Jadeja was aiming for the rough. Muthusamy gets his front foot out and looks to pad it away. Jadeja and the Indian players put in a stifled appeal. The ball goes behind and it looks like the umpire has turned it down but then the umpire raises his finger. Muthusamy has a word with Faf du Plessis and then refers it upstairs. Replay rolls in and shows the impact was outside but as Senuran was not offering any shot that is not an issue. The Ball Tracker then shows the ball was going onto hit the stumps. Muthusamy has to walk back to the pavilion for the first time as this is his first dismissal in the series. Replays later on show Jadeja was not even appealing. He had his hand on his head and was surprised and delighted when the umpire had raised his finger. South Africa lose one of their two reviews.
On the stumps, Philander keeps it out.
On the pads, Vernon glances it to square leg.
Floated on the stumps, Vernon defends it off the front foot.
Play and misses. Tossed up outside off, Vernon looks to drive but misses.
On off, du Plessis defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Faf keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Faf goes on his back foot and defends it onto the ground.
Faf lunges forward and defends this one as well.
On the stumps, Faf blocks it.
Flighted on the pads, Faf glances it to square leg.
Beauty! Jadeja gives this air outside off, Philander looks to defend but the ball keeps straight and goes past the outside edge.
Tossed up on the stumps, Philander defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Vernon leaves it alone.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Gives it air on off, VP blocks it.
Away from the off stump asking Philander to drive. Vernon though has no mood to play that.
Flatter one on the off pole line, tucked towards short leg.
Fuller one on off, pushed towards extra cover.
On the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket for a single by du Plessis.
Flatter one just outside off, blocked out.
Shortish just outside off, defended from within the crease.
Floated on middle and off, Faf plants his front foot forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated around off, Faf keeps it out.
FOUR! Faf breaks the shackles! Floated around off, du Plessis smashes it over mid on for a boundary.
Faf follows the boundary with a calm defense.
Tossed up outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.

Haha! This is funny and also serious. Shorter around off, Faf looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him on the pad. The Indian players go up in appeal. Jadeja comes in between the wicket and appeals. His foot though gets stuck and he falls over. The umpire has a smile but also gives Jadeja the FIRST OFFICIAL WARNING for going into the danger area.

This has turned from South to North. Floated around off, Faf looks to drive but misses, The ball spins away and goes to the left of first slip. Rahane dives to that side and collects it superbly with one hand.
Another beauty! Flighted around off, Philander looks to defend but gets squared up.
Tossed up around off, Vernon looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shorter on off, Philander defends it off the back foot.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted on middle, Vernon drives it straight but Ashwin stops it with his right hand. The ball deflects behind but Faf says no for a run.

That could have been disastrous. Floated on off, Philander pushes it towards cover and calls for a quick run. Faf though sends him back. Vernon manages to get back in time but when he came out he was in the danger area. No official warning though.
Floated on the stumps, defended by du Plessis.
Flighted on off, du Plessis defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Faf pushes it to cover.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Solidly defended by Philander.
Stop the press! Philander is off the mark. Tossed up on off, Vernon pushes it towards mid off and keeps the strike.
Flighted on off, Philander defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Philander blocks it out.
Shorter on off, Vernon goes on his back foot and blocks it.
Philander bends his back and blocks it out.
Slightly shorter on off, Philander glances it towards square leg.
Tossed up outside off, Philander shoulders arms to it. The ball kisses his pad and goes behind. But no run can be taken or will be counted as he was not offering any shot.
Slightly short outside off, pushed to the cover region for a single.
Flatter one on off, pushed towards the point fielder. A little bit of yes no about taking the run but in the end they decide against it.
Philander blocks this one off the front foot.
Philander opens the face of the bat and guides this one towards backward point.
Floated on middle and off, Philander has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Pushes this one towards silly mid off.
On middle and off, pushed towards mid on.
Philander defends this one onto the pitch.
FOUR! First boundary for Philander! On the pads, he flicks this one wide of the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. 150 comes up for South Africa.
Philander defends this one out off the back foot.
Outside off, pushed towards the man at point by Vernon.
Flatter and a touch outside off, Philander blocks this one from within the crease.
Full and wide outside off, driven towards sweeper cover for a single.
Flatter and on off, Philander defends this one on the ground.
Philander edges that one towards the man at point.
Full and floated on middle and off, Philander pushes it towards mid off.
Philander pushes this one back to the bowler.
Dabs this one towards silly point. Good over by Jadeja.
Floated on middle and off by Rohit, Faf pushes it back to him.
Du Plessis defends this one from within the crease.
On the leg side, du Plessis tucks this one towards the leg side.
Du Plessis blocks this one towards the leg side.
Faf defends this one onto the pitch.
Touch shorter on middle and off, du Plessis defends it from within the crease.
Philander goes deep in his crease and blocks it out.
FOUR! Full and floated on off, Philander drives this one through the cover region. Ishant gives this a chase but cannot keep the ball in play. Boundary signalled.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Philander defends this one towards the off side.
FOUR! Now down the ground! Full and on middle and off, Philander drives this one and the ball races through mid off to the fence.
Full and floated on middle and off, Vernon pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler.
Now floated on middle and off, pushed back again towards Jadeja.
Excellent fielding! Floated outside off, du Plessis lunges forward and drives this one towards cover. Mayank Agarwal at short extra cover dives to his right and stops it going past him with one hand.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads, du Plessis flicks this one towards mid-wicket for a single.
Philander defends this one off the front foot.
Full and floated on off, du Plessis looks to defend but fails. The ball hits his pads and the Indians appeal. However, the umpire is unmoved and India do not go for the review. Maybe going down leg.
Du Plessis plays that off the front foot and into the ground.

OUT! CAUGHT! Beauty by Ashwin! Take a bow! He has bamboozled Faf du Plessis completely! The skipper departs and the South African resistance looks to be coming to an end. Floated just outside, the ball pitches in the rough. It has a touch of extra spin and bounce on it. Du Plessis looks to defend it but the ball goes off the outside edge towards Rahane at first slip who makes no mistake. South Africa 8 down now and no recognised batters left in the lineup now.
Jaffa again! Maharaj plays for the turn but this kept on going straight and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Maharaj gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it out.
Maharaj defends this off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Philander pushes this one towards the cover region and takes a single as Mayank cannot gather it in the first attempt.
Maharaj pushes this one towards the mid off region.
FOUR! On the pads of Maharaj, he works it towards the fine leg region for a boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Maharaj defends this one towards the leg side.
Last ball of the over, Maharaj pushes this one back towards Jadeja.
Philander pushes this one back to the bowler.
Philander comes onto the front foot and pushes this one towards mid on.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated outside off, pushed towards the cover region for a single.
Floated on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.
On the pads, Maharaj flicks it towards the leg side but straight to the man.
Philander comes onto the front foot and blocks it out.
Full and floated outside off, Philander pushes this one towards the cover region.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Philander prods forward and defends this one out.
Philander looks to defend but the ball goes off his inside edge towards fine leg and the batters take one.
Maharaj comes forward and defends it.
Philander prods forward and blocks it out.
Good fielding! Philander flicks this one powerfully towards mid-wicket but the man at short mid-wicket dives and stops it.
On the pads of Philander, flicks this one towards mid-wicket for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads, Maharaj tickles this one towards fine leg.
Jaffa! This delivery is reminiscent to the one on which du Plessis got dismissed but Maharaj survives as the ball misses the outside edge of Maharaj's bat.
Length ball on middle and off, Philander tucks it towards the leg side.
Philander tries to slash at this length delivery but it goes off the bottom edge towards the bowler.
Length ball angling in, Philander defends this one out.
Philander defends this one off the back foot towards extra cover.
Philander pushes this one towards mid on and takes a single.
Length ball on middle and off, Maharaj blocks this one out.
Philander defends this one towards mid off.
Goes onto the back foot and guides this one towards backward point.
Philander shows the full face and defends this one off the back foot.
On the pads of Philander, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Philander defends this one off the front foot watchfully.
Philander outside edges this one towards the off side.
Length ball just outside off, Maharaj confidenty leaves this one alone.
Maharaj tries to defend this good length ball but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Maharaj ducks under it.
Mightily close to the off pole this! Length ball just outside off, tailing back in. Maharaj shoulders arms but the ball almost shaves the off pole. Close call!
FOUR LEG BYES! Down the leg side, Maharaj tries to flick this  one off the pads but misses. The ball kisses the pads and rolls towards fine leg for four leg byes.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on off, Philander looks to drive but it goes off the bottom half to the off side and they take a single.
Tossed up on the pads, Maharaj glances it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted on off, Philander looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes to point.
Flighted on off, Philander keeps it out.
On off, Philander keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Philander does well to keep it out.
FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Maharaj cuts this one towards backward point for a boundary. Good resistance by the tailenders here.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked out.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards the man at cover.
Yorker down the leg side, Maharaj tries to tickle it fine down the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
Maharaj pushes this one towards the cover region off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Maharaj pushes this one towards the off side.
Floated outside off, pushed towards cover.
Philander plays this one towards cover-point.
Philander cuts this one towards the point region.
Philander defends this one back towards the bowler.
Philander blocks this one off the front foot.
Jadeja bowls this one outside off, Philander leaves it alone.
Darts this one on the off pole, Maharaj pushes this one towards long on for a single.
On the pads, flicked towards square leg.
Floated on middle and leg, Philander inside edges this one onto the pads.
Philander prods forward and looks to defend. It goes off the inside edge towards Mayank Agarwal at short leg on the bounce. The ball goes between his legs towards mid-wicket for a single.
Maharaj defends this one off the back foot.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on middle and leg, Philander defends it to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Vernon keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, VP keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Vernon looks defend but gets a outside edge towards point.
Floated on the stumps, Philander defends it.
