Darts one just outside off, Maharaj blocks it out.
Outside off, watchfully defended.
Maharaj prods forward and blocks it onto the pitch.
Maharaj defends this one onto the pitch off the back foot.
Maharaj has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads, Maharaj flicks this in front of square leg for a single.
Short of a length ball outside off, cut towards the point region. Pujara hares after it and keeps it down to two.
Maharaj has defended it off the back foot.
Floated just outside off, Maharaj plays for the spin but the ball kept on going straight beating the outside edge of Maharaj's blade.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Maharaj defends this one out watchfully.
FOUR! Maharaj drives this one past the bowler superbly. It goes through the mid off region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Philander flicks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Good length ball on off, Philander goes for the drive but due to the away movement on it he misses it completely. The ball goes to the keeper on the bounce.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball on middle and off, Philander leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, Philander tickles it towards fine leg for a single.

Shami bowls a full ball, angling into the batter. Maharaj looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The Indian players put in a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Maybe going down leg? Yes, the Ball Tracker confirms it.
Floated on off, pushed towards the cover region.
Full and outside off, pushed towards the cover region again. The fielder there dives to his left and saves runs for his side.
Another floated ball on off, Philander outside edges it towards the slip cordon but it goes on the bounce. The key to it was playing with soft hands.
Floated outside off, the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip on the bounce.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Philander has pushed this straight back to the bowler.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
FOUR! Pulled away handsomely by Maharaj! Short of a length ball outside off, Maharaj rocks back and pulls this one through square leg for a boundary.
Shami straightaway looks to attack the stumps after that halt in play but Maharaj is solid in his defense.
Full ball just outside off, Maharaj defends this one off the front foot.
Full and wide outside off, Maharaj pushes this one towards the off side.
How has Maharaj kept that out? Corker of a yorker by Shami, on the middle and leg pole line, Maharaj digs it out at the last moment towards mid on.
Philander defends this one out.
Philander watchfully blocks it out.

Full and floated on off, Philander pushes this one towards long off for a single. However, Ashwin there is slow to get to the ball and that allows the batters to take the second. Bad fielding but very good awareness by the South African batters!
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and floated on off again, Philander prods forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge on it. However, it goes on the bounce to the fielder at first slip.
Flatter on middle and off, Philander looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Good length ball, nipping into Maharaj. He blocks it by coming onto the front foot.
Length ball on middle and off, Maharaj blocks it out.
Goes for the shorter one this time, down the leg side. Maharaj ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards cover.
Length ball outside off, Maharaj initially looks to play at it but then leaves it alone.
First over after Tea well negotiated by Maharaj. He blocks this length ball on the off pole line back towards the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Philander pushes it to mid off for one.
Lovely ball. Tossed up on off, Maharaj comes forward to defend it but the ball spins away missing the outside edge of the bat.
FOUR! Maharaj decides enough of leaving and defending. He has taken the aerial route. Flighted on off and middle, Maharaj swings his bat and lofts it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
On the pads, Keshav glances it to the on side for a single.
Floated on off, VP blocks it.
Away from the off pole, Vernon shoulders arms to it.
Length ball outside off, little to no reverse swing. Maharaj leaves it alone.
On the pads, Keshav glances it to the on side and gets a single.
Back of a length ball outside off, Philander has nothing to do with it.
Good length ball on off, Vernon defends it towards cover-point and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Full on off, Vernon defends it by bending his back.
FOUR! Good ball but wonderfully played. Full and it zips in off the deck. Philander drives it sweetly wide of Ishant Sharma at mid on for a boundary.

FOUR! The ball is following Ishant everywhere. Short around off, Maharaj gets on his back foot and cuts it nicely through point. Ishant goes behind it from backward point but he knew he was always going to come second so he withdraws. Pujara from cover goes and brings the ball back from the fence.
Tossed up on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, Maharaj leaves it alone.
Floated around off, Keshav looks to defend it inside the line but misses.
Maharaj lunges forward and blocks this tossed up ball to get through the over.
Good length ball pitching on off, it comes in with the angle. Philander looks to defend but he does so off the upper half of his bat.
Good leave! Length delivery outside off. It is an inswinger but Philander is aware of his off stump and leaves it alone. The ball was not far away from the stump though.
Length delivery on middle and leg, Vernon looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pad. The new, hard ball seems to be intimidating him.
Another good ball. Length ball on off and middle, Philanderr looks to defend but does so off the outer half of his bat as the ball zips away.
Length delivery outside off, Philander leaves it late.
FOUR! This will give Philander more confidence to play against the new ball. Slightly fuller around off, Vernon drives it through point for a boundary.

Ishant starts his new spell with a fuller ball outside off. Maharaj initially looks to play but then changes his mind. Too late though as the ball hits the inside edge of the bat. It bounces away from the off stump and goes to the keeper.
Good length ball around off, Maharaj drives it on the up to mid off.
Ishant sprays one down the leg side. Maharaj looks to flick but misses.
Bouncer! A wayward one though as this one is down the leg side.
Good length ball on off, Keshav looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR LEG BYES! Ishant bowls another one down the leg side, Maharaj looks to flick but it goes off his pad fine down the leg side. It is wide of Saha who was diving to his left and races away to the fence.

This is what a hard ball does. Good length ball on off, the ball shoots off the surface. It hits the upper half of Philander's bat and flies uppishly towards the long leg fielder where he takes it on the bounce. The batters take a single.

Play and a miss. Length delivery on top of off, Maharaj looks to pull but the ball does not rise as much as he expected and he misses it. Mayank Agarwal standing in the close-in position chirps a loud 'aye'.
Bouncer! Maharaj ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Wild from Maharaj. Good length ball outside off, Keshav swings his bat at it but misses.
Back of a length ball on off, Maharaj defends it to get through the over.

Direct hit and that could have been trouble. Fuller around off, Philander pushes it towards cover and calls for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Saha fails to gather it too but that does not cost any extra run.
Azharuddin-esque fielding from Ishant. Back of a length ball around the body, Maharaj defends it and calls for a single. Ishant gets to the ball quickly and does a no look throw.
Outside off, Philander leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Vernon pushes it to cover.
Fuller on off, VP defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball around off, the ball swings in after pitching. Philander does well to defend it off the outer half of his bat.
Ouch that must have hurt. Back of a length ball around the body, Maharaj hops and does well to keep it down. Even though it hit his glove it went wide of short leg.
Bouncer! Maharaj ducks under it.
Length ball on off, KM defends it towards cover and takes a single. He is feeling his right shoulder as the ball jarred his bat.
Bouncer again. This one is to Philander. Vernon sways away from it.
Good length ball on off, Philander defends it to the off side.
On the fourth stump line, Vernon leaves it alone.
Very full on middle and leg. Keshav defends it towards mid off. The length of the ball created some excitement in the cubical.
Length ball on off, Maharaj defends it with a dead-bat.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, Maharaj nudges it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Good length delivery on off, Philander defends it towards cover and shouts a loud no.

A better release might have put Philandeer in trouble. Fuller on middle and off, Vernon pushes it to the left of mid on and scampers through for a single. Umesh yadav there gets to the ball quickly but cannot release it proeprly allowing Philander to get back in with ease.
FOUR! Educational edge!  Good length ball on off, Maharaj looks to defend but it goes off the edge through the vacant gully region for a boundary.
Floated on off, Philander keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Vernon bends his back and keeps it away.
Tossed up outside off, Vernon defends it onto the ground.
Flights one on off, Philander strokes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Philander keeps it away.
On the stumps, Philander defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Slightly quicker on middle and off, Maharaj strokes it through cover a single. This one kept a bit low.
Floated on off, Philander looks to defend but it goes off the edge wide of slip for a single.
On the pads, Maharaj flicks it to square leg.
FOUR! Creamed away. Tossed up on off, Maharaj smashes it through mid off for a boundary.
Floated on off, Maharaj defends it onto the ground.
Philander defends it off the front foot with soft hands towards cover and gets a single.
Shorter around off, Maharaj punches it to the off side and gets to the other end.
Spin and bounce. Flighted around off, Philander plants his front foot out and tries to defend it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On middle and off, Philander looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up on the stumps, Vernon defends it off the front foot.
DROPPED! Tough chance but could have been taken! Floated on middle, Maharaj punches it uppishly to the right of Ashwin. He dives to that side and gets his hand to the ball but cannot bask it in.
FOUR! Maharaj gets to his best Test score in style. Shorter on off, Maharaj punches it through cover-point for a boundary.
Now Maharaj calmly blocks this ball.

FIFTY FOR MAHARAJ! Champion stuff from him. Yes we have seen brilliant knock from the Indian batters but this innings cannot be looked past just like that. He was nursing a shoulder injury but he has fought it out in the middle like a warrior. Tossed up ball on middle, Keshav glances it towards cow corner and calls for two straight away. Philander responds, taking Maharaj to his maiden Test fifty. He raises his bat as his family, teammates and the crowd applauds his courageous fight.
Maharaj gets back in his zone and defends it solidly.
Tossed up on off, Keshav looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Darted on the off pole, pushed back towards the bowler.
That one shoots up after pitching. Philander tries to block it and manages to do so off the splice of his bat.
Outside off, watchfully defended.
Desperation for the Indians and now it is showing. Floated on off, Philander blocks it out. The Indians put in a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Replays show no pad involved.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Short and wide outside off, Maharaj cuts this towards backward point and Pujara gives it the chase. Keeps the ball in play and the batters take two.

This time a better appeal! Floated outside off, spinning in. Maharaj looks to block but misses. He is hit on the pad. The Indians appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The replays show that the impact is outside off.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Maharaj pushes this one towards gully and takes a quick single.
Plays a square cut. The ball goes towards the point region and the batters take one.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. They have run through for a single.
Maharaj mistimes his lofted shot over mid on. The ball luckily for him clears the fielder in the circle there and the batters are able to take one.
On the pads, Maharaj flicks it towards the leg side.
Maharaj defends this one off the back foot.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Maharaj defends it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads of Maharaj, he flicks this one towards square leg for a couple.
Floats one outside off, Philander misses his defense and is hit on the pads.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Philander looks to drive at this one but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads. It lobs towards Ashwin but falls well short of him.
Philander defends this one off the back foot.
Pitched way wide outside off, Philander leaves it alone.
Philander gets another inside edge onto the pads. Does well to negotiate the over.
Good length ball on middle and off, blocked out.
On the pads, Maharaj flicks it fine towards the leg side and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
Another good length ball outside off, pushed towards the man at cover-point.
Philander comes onto the front foot and blocks it out again.
Full delivery outside off, pushed towards the man at extra-cover.
Darted on the off pole, Maharaj blocks it out.
Outside off, left alone by Maharaj.
Maharaj gets onto the front foot and defends it onto the pitch.
EDGED AND FOUR! Shortish delivery outside off, Maharaj has a slash at it but the ball goes off the outside edge into the third man fence.

FOUR! 100-run stand up between Maharaj and Philander! Two warriors from South Africa have stood up and frustrated India. Another short ball outside off, this time Maharaj connects well and the ball races to the point boundary. They have given some joy to the Proteas fans. This is the highest 9th wicket stand for South Africa against India.
The batsman has punched that ball through the offside.
FOUR! Gorgeous drive! Full and outside off, Philander just leans into the drive and creams this one through the cover region. Nothing like a tailender this.
Down the leg side, Philander looks to flick it but misses.
Bouncer on middle and off, Philander sways away from it.
Another bouncer, Philander does well to evade it.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on middle and off, Maharaj pushes it back towards the bowler.

Close one! Good awareness by Maharaj! He goes back in his crease, defends it off the back foot. The ball bounces inside the crease and is going onto the stumps. Maharaj knows exactly where the ball is and just pushes it away with his bat behind the keeper.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Maharaj goes deep into his crease and blocks this one out.
Keshav goes deep in his crease again to block it out.
Maharaj pushes this one towards the mid off region.
Philander goes back in his crease and defend it towards the leg side.
Philander drives this one towards mid on but straight to the man.
Philander defends this one onto the pitch.
Philander looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads towards the leg side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Philander defends this one onto the pitch.
Maharaj watchfully defends this one out.
EDGED AND FOUR! Fortune favours the brave and that is what is happening here. Shortish outside off, Maharaj edges this one. The ball flies wide of first slip and into the third man fence.
Maharaj prods forward and defends this one.
Floated on middle and off, pushed towards mid off.
Maharaj drives this one through mid off and takes a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Maharaj goes back in his crease and blocks this one out.
Maharaj prods forward and looks to defend this one. The ball comes off the inside edge and hits the batsman on the pads. India put in a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally the resistance of South Africa is broken and Ashwin is the man to provide the breakthrough! Ashwin bowls a floated one on the pads, Maharaj looks to flick it down the leg side. He connects but does so uppishly. The leg slip fielder is perfectly positioned and takes the catch there. Rohit Sharma takes a dolly and he is getting hugs from all his teammates. A brilliant, gritty and fighting knock from Keshav Maharaj comes to an end.
On middle and leg, Rabada just manages to get his bat on it. He flicks it down the leg side, fine. The fielder in the deep mops it up and the batters take two.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Full and floated on middle, Philander looks to defend but fails to do so. The Indian players put in an appeal but nothing from the umpire. The ball goes towards silly point. Replays roll in and show that the ball had taken an inside way before thudding onto the pads and going towards silly point.
Flighted on off, Philander defends it off the front foot.
Beauty from Jadeja. Tossed up around off, Philander looks to defend but the ball turns away and squares him up.
Gives this air on off, Philander blocks it.
Flighted on off, Philander defends it with soft hands towards cover and gets to the other end.

SAFE! Nothing on the Ultra Edge and India lose one of their 2 reviews. Flighted outside off, Rabada looks to drive but the ball spins in and goes to the keeper. Saha fumbles but then takes the catch. Jadeja and Saha put in an appeal. The convince Kohli to take it upstairs. The Indian skipper obliges. Replay roll in and it shows nothing on the Ultra Edge.
Floated on middle and off, turning in. Philander comes forward looking to block and fails to do so. He is hit on the stomach as he misses the ball.
Philander comes forward and defends it onto the ground.
Floated just outside off, defended watchfully.
Philander pushes this one towards long on and takes a single.
Rabada comes onto the front foot and the full face of the bat to block it out.
Pushed towards mid on off the front foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Philander comes onto the front foot and defends it.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Philander comes forward and defends it onto the pitch.
Outside off, pushed towards extra cover.
Another one outside off, blocked onto the off side.
Rabada defends this one back towards the bowler.
Jaffa! Floated just outside off, Rabada looks to defend but the ball spins away and beats the outside edge of Rabada's blade.
Floated outside off, Rabada edges that one. It goes uppishly towards point.

OUT! LBW! Rabada is the last wicket to fall and finally, after some stubborn resistance, South Africa have been dismissed for 275. Ashwin gets his 4th wicket of the innings and India will be mightily pleased to know that this innings has ended today itself. Ashwin floats this one on the middle pole line, it pitches and straightens but not enough to meet Rabada's blade as he plays outside the line. The ball hits him on the pad, India appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Rabada straightaway goes for the review knowing he is the last man at the crease. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracker comes into play and shows the ball to be hitting the leg pole. This is the 50th Test wicket for Ravichandran Ashwin against South Africa. That will be the last ball of the day as the umpire takes the bails off. STUMPS, DAY 3!

Excellent delivery to start the innings. Ishant starts with a good length ball outside off, it comes back in viciously. Markram offers a dangerous leave but as they say, if you leave and it does not hit you then it is a good leave.

OUT! LBW! India start with a bang! The first one was on a length and came back in. Markram was lucky to survive that but on this occasion he is not. Ishant goes slightly fuller and once again gets the ball in to the right-hander. Markram looks to defend but the ball hits him on high on the pads. The Indian players go up in a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Markram has a word with his partner, Elgar. Dean does not look sure and just when Markram was about to review the timer gets to zero. Markram's first pair in Tests. Ishant gets his first wicket of the game. Well hold on, Ball Tracker later on rolls in and it is a disappointing news for Markram, Elgar and the whole of South Africa. The Ball Tracker shows the ball was going onto miss the stumps.
Ohh! Full and this one comes back in sharply too. De Bruyn does well to defend it off the front foot.
On the fourth stump line, Theunis lets it carry to the keeper.
Another one outside off, Theunis shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on off, Theunis defends it to get through the over. Wicket maiden for Ishant to start the innings.
Umesh starts with a length delivery on off, Elgar starts his innings with a back foot defense.

Could have been disastrous for South Africa. Back of a length ball on off, Elgar defends it with soft hands towards cover-point and calls for a quick single. Theunis responds but he knows it is a suicidal run. Mayank Agarwal gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. A direct hit and Theunis would've been walking into the pavilion.

EDGED AND FOUR! Length delivery around off, Theunis looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes off the outside edge. It falls short of Virat Kohli at third slip and goes through him for a boundary.
Length delivery outside off, Theunis leaves it alone.
Once again Theunis does not go chasing after the ball away from the stump.
FOUR! Streaky! Fuller around off, de Bruyn looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of the diving Rahane at gully for a boundary.
Comes around the wicket and bowls it on a length outside off, Dean leaves it alone. Late swing for Ishant.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar does not go chasing after it.
Ishant continues to bowl outside off to Elgar. He once again calmly leaves it.
Ishant comes closer to the off pole, Elgar defends it off the front foot.
Goes wide of the off stump again, does Ishant. Dean Elgar shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on off, Elgar defends it to get through the over.

Nice swing and carry on this one. Good length ball just around off, it moves away off the surface. Theunis shoulders arms to it. The ball goes to Saha at chest height. Seldom you see such carry for pacers in India.
Good length delivery outside off, Theunis leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, de Bruyn does not disturb that.
Goes fuller around off, Theunis defends it towards point.

FOUR BYES! Poor ball from Umesh. He misses his line and bowls one down the leg side. Theunis looks to flick but misses. The ball keeps on going with the angle as even Saha, who was diving to his left cannot save it. The idea was right to surprise him with a ball on middle and leg after going in and around off but the execution was not.
Good length ball on off, de Bruyn defends it to get through a good over of Umesh.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar calmly leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! Third boundary of the innings and all three have come off the outside edge. Slightly fuller around off, Elgar looks to defend it with soft hands but the ball takes the outside edge. The ball goes right between gully and third slip and the ball goes away to the fence. Rahane dives but cannot get his hand to it as the ball was well wide.
On off, Elgar keeps it out.

Another edge that does not carry. If you're thinking the slip should come in then that will be difficult as there is good carry. Length ball on off, Elgar looks to defend with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge. The fact that he played it with soft hands worked in his favour as that was the reason the ball did not carry to Kohli at third slip.

EDGED AND FOUR! Another boundary off the edge. Fuller around off, it zips away after pitching. Elgar goes for it in a wild way and the ball takes a fat outside edge of his willow and goes uppishly wide of gully for a boundary.
Around off, Elgar this time calmly defends it.
Umesh continues to bowl outside off to Theunis. De Bruyn leaves it alone.
Fuller and closer to off, de Bruyn defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Theunis pushes it to point.

OUT! Caught! Brilliant catch from Wridhimann Saha  and smart bowling from Umesh. He was bowling in and around off and then he surprises Theunis with a one down the leg side. He tried it in the last over but that was way down, this one is closer to the body. De Bruyn looks to flick but the ball kisses his bat and goes to the left of the keeper. Saha dives to that side and takes a one-handed stunner. If you were wondering why Saha was picked over Pant, then this catch is the reason. He is hailed as one of the best keepers in the world and this is a proof of it. South Africa in all sorts of trouble. 2 down in the 6th over of the day.
Another one down the leg side, Faf though does not get any bat on it as he misses his flick.
Good length ball outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.
In the air but safe again. Elgar continues to ride his luck. Short ball closer to the body, Elgar looks to pull but it goes off the upper half of his bat wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball around off, Elgar punches it towards point and gets to the other end.
Good ball and a good  leave. Outside off and it comes in off the deck. Faf shows awareness of his off pole and offers a very good leave.
On the pads, Faf looks to flick but it goes off the inner half of his bat through square leg for a couple. Du Plessis is off the mark but not in the most convincing manner. The trail now is 300.
Another gem of a delivery. Fuller around off and middle, du Plessis looks to defend but it jags back in and takes the inside edge of the bat and goes behind square on the leg side.
Fuller on off, du Plessis keeps it out.
Well played. Slightly fuller delivery outside off, Elgar plays it nicely through point. Mayank gives it a chase and saves it with a dive before the ropes. Two taken.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller on off, Elgar pushes it wide of point. Jadeja, who is lightning quick gets to the ball quickly showing his athleticism.
Length delivery around off, Elgar defends it off his back foot towards point.
Fuller on middle, Elgar pushes it wide of mid on for a single.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Around off, Dean defends it towards backward point.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ishant. He strays down on the pads. These are easy pickings for Elgar. He just eases his flick through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
Another one on the pads, Elgar does not time his flick well this time. Ashwin runs to his right from square leg and keeps it to a dot with a dive.
Length ball on off, Elgar works it to square leg and shouts a loud no.
Fuller around off, Elgar blocks it.
Misses his length on the first ball of the new over, does Umesh. Strays the ball on the leg side. Faf goes for a flick but misses.
Length on middle, Faf this time tucks it behind square for a single.
Good length ball angled in to the batter, Dean stands tall to keep it out.
Too wide to make the batter play this time. Elgar shoulders arms.
On the pads again, Elgar glances it through fine leg to change ends.
On the fourth stump line, Faf lets it be.

Shami comes and straightaway there is excitment. He starts with a bouncer. It is around off, Elgar looks to pull but then decides to pull away from the shot. He ends up lobbing up off the upper half of his bat. Luckily for Elgar it falls in no man's land on the on side.
FOUR! Good shot! Fuller around off, Elgar strokes it through point for a boundary.

FOUR! First boundary off the cover drive in this innings. Fuller around off, Elgar gets on his front foot and creams it through cover. Cover drives are always beautiful but when a southpaw hits it they look even better.
After back-to-back boundaries, Elgar calmly defends this one.
FOUR! Slammed through point. Fuller outside off, Elgar plants his front foot forward and leans the drive through point for a boundary.
Fuller on off, Elgar blocks it to get through the over. 12 off Shami's first. Expensive start for him.
Floated on middle and leg, Faf looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat to the on side for a single.
Tossed up on the pads, Elgar turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Shorter on off, Faf defends it off the back foot.
Floated on off, du Plessis keeps it out.

Ouch! That must have hurt. Tossed up on middle and off, Faf gets down on one knee and hits the sweep shot hard. Rohit Sharma at short leg, turns away and the ball hits him on his lower calf. Rohit is fine to continue though.
Floated on off, the ball turns in a lot. Faf looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.

FOUR! Nicely guided through point and gully. Fullish length on the fourth stump line, Elgar comes forward and guides the ball with an angled bat. The ball races to the third man fence. The boundary brings 50 up for the Proteas.
Bumper but too high. Elgar leaves it alone.
Wide! Another bouncer! Elgar again ducks under it as it is too high. Called wide as well by the umpire so Shami has to re-bowl that ball.

Beaten! Or is it? Saha feels there is an edge. Rohit is not sure through. Kohli is asking Saha if he heard anything. Should they go for the DRS or not? They don't eventually and lucky that they did not opt for it as the Ultra Edge arrived to show no tickle. It was a good length ball outside off, Elgar went for the drive but misses. Lucky not to edge that one.
Beauty again but no edge! Good length ball around off which seams away after pitching just a hint. Elgar has a push but misses.
Closer to off pole, Elgar keeps it out.
Fuller on the pads, Elgar pushes it back to the bowler. Shami picks the ball and has a shy at the striker's end. He misses but had he hit it wouldn't have mattered.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Loopy ball on middle, tucked towards short leg
Flighted ball around off, Faf pushes it back to the bowler.
Another flighted ball around middle, the ball goes towards point off the outer half of the bat of Faf.
Landed around off, Faf pushes it towards cover to change ends.
Fuller ball around off, Elgar pushes it to the right of Ashwin.
Length ball angled in to the right-hander. Faf keeps it out of the back foot.
Shami is targeting the stumps as he dishes this fullish length ball on off, Faf defends it out.
Goes wide this time. Too wide for Faf to make any attempt to play a shot.
On the fifth stump line this time. Faf makes another leave.
Late swing there! Another length ball in the channel of uncertainty. Faf leaves it alone. The ball kept slightly low this time and died down ahead of Saha behind the wicket.

Jaffa! Almost gets Shami a wicket. Pitches it on a good length and closer to the off pole. Du Plessis is rooted to his crease as he looks to defend. The ball whizzes past the outside edge. Kohli enjoyed that ball.
Ashwin floats this around off, Elgar drives it straight to extra cover.
This time he lands it outside off, it turns away as Elgar leaves it alone.
A quicker one outside off, Elgar leaves it alone again.
Misses his line this time. Lands it on middle which turns down the leg side. Elgar misses his flick.
On the pads again, Elgar looks to work it down the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads.

FOUR BYES! Ashwin flights this one around off which turns away after landing around off. Elgar goes for the drive through covers but due to the away turn he can't get bat on ball. Rahane dives to his right to field but the ball races to the third man fence.
Good length ball outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Gets closer to the off pole, du Plessis keeps it out.
Length ball around off, Faf blocks it towards mid off.
Good length ball on the fourth stump line, du Plessis covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish length ball in the channel outside off, the Protea skipper makes another leave.
Around off, Faf keeps it out by standing tall and defending it towards cover. Another tight over from Shami, back-to-back maidens from him.
Floats it on middle, Elgar blocks it out.
On middle again, pushed towards cover this time.
On the pads on a fullish length, tucked towards mid-wicket for a run.

NOT OUT! The impact saves the Protea skipper. Ashwin floats this around off, Faf goes for the sweep but can't connect and is hit on the pads. Ashwin and India appeal but the umpire does not agree. Ashwin is not sure but Saha it seems is confident and Kohli goes for the review. Here comes the Ball Tracker, the impact is umpire's call and hence it doesn't matter even if the ball is hitting the timbers. An excellent review from the Indians because that was marginal. Had Faf been adjudged LBW he would have had to walk back but not the case though.
Floated on middle and leg, Faf flicks it through mid-wicket. There was an easy single on offer but for some reason du Plessis does not take it.
Tossed up on off, Faf keeps it out.
FOUR! Not the welcome Jadeja would have looked for. Flighted around off, Elgra gets on his front foot and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up fuller outside off, Elgar looks to play it on the off side but the ball hits the inner half of his bat and goes to the on side.
Flighted on off, Elgar keeps it out.
Floated on off, Elgar plants his front foot forward and blocks it.
On off, Elgar defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on the pads, Dean tucks it to square leg.
On middle this time, Faf guides it towards square leg.
Beaten! Good ball that. Saha catches it well on the second attempt. Ashwin lands it around off, Faf looks to block but is beaten. Saha appeals but nothing from the others.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On off, Faf tucks it right of the short leg fielder uppishly.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Fullish ball on middle, Elgar eases it through mid on for a single.
Fuller ball on off, pushed towards cover.
Another fuller ball around off, Faf looks to defend but the ball takes an outside edge and goes to the second slip on the bounce.
Jadeja fires this one on the pads, Faf looks to work it down the leg side but misses. The ball goes towards short fine leg for a single.
On the pads this time, Elgar tucks it towards mid-wicket and changes end.

Nicely bowled! Huge appeal from the Indians but umpire is not moved. Floats it around off, Elgar looks to defends but the ball hits his pad and lobs towards Rahane who dives to pouch that catch. Indians appeal but not out says the umpire. Ultra Edge rolls in and looks like there is a spike but Rahane himself was not sure.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, Faf keeps it out.
Fullish ball on middle, du Plessis keeps it out.
Fullish length ball, Faf sweeps for a single.
Shortish length, Faf blocks it off the back foot.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Tossed up around off, Elgar looks to sweep but misses. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire says no.
Shorter on off, Elgar glances it to square leg.
Floated on middle and leg, Elgar sweeps it fine down the leg side for a single.
Flatter on off, Faf defends it off the front foot.
Beauty! Jadeja gives this one air on off, Faf looks to defend but the ball turns away and squares up the South African skipper.
Around off, Faf defends it off the front foot.
Flighted ball on middle, Elgar keeps it out.

Fuller ball around off, Elgar drives it through covers for a single. Umesh at deep cover fields the ball and throws it to Ashwin who can't gather the ball due to extra bounce and they concede a couple as overthrow.

OUT! CAUGHT! Saha you beauty. What a blinder that from the wicket keeper. Faf du Plessis has to walk back. Ashwin fires this one closer to the off pole, Faf looks to defend but the ball takes an inside edge, hits the back thigh and goes to Saha behind the wicket very quickly. Saha there fumbles a bit but does well to keep the ball in the air, once, twice, thrice and then in the fourth attempt he gobbles it diving forward. Excellent work from Saha and he continues to prove why Kohli terms him as the best keeper of the country. Just 5 runs off 54 balls for the Protea skipper. His long vigil ends and the situation for South Africa worsen further. 10 minutes to go for Lunch. Can India strike one more time?
Flighted ball around off, Bavuma pushes it towards short third man.
Beaten! A quicker one around off, Bavuma looks to defend but is beaten.
Flighted ball around off, Bavuma pads it away.
Floated on off, Elgar glances it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, Elgar defends it let towards slip.
Gives this air around off, Elgar glances it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Gives this air on off, Bavuma defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on off, Bavuma defends it off his front foot in a textbook fashion.
Flighted on off, Temba keeps it out.
Flights this around off, Elgar drives but can't beat Kohli at short extra cover.

OUT! Elgar has thrown it away! With Lunch minutes away, all he had to do was to get through the overs. Ashwin flights this one around off, Elgar looks to play it over the bowler's head but the ball takes the outside edge and lobs high past mid off. Umesh Yadav runs behind to his right, gets under the ball but fumbles twice before catching it cleanly. Elgar heads to the pavilion, two short of his half ton. Wicket number two for Ashwin.
Around off this time Bavuma turns it towards point with an angled bat.
Bavuma this time lunges forward to block this fullish length ball.
Another full ball, Bavuma this time pushes it towards cover-point to get off the mark.
Around off, de Kock blocks it out.
Fuller ball on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fires it on middle, de Kock flicks it uppishly but wide of the short leg fielder. De Kock gets his first run of the innings.
Around off, Bavuma keeps it out.
Fuller again, Bavuma defends it out.
Around off on a fullish length, driven towards mid off.
Fuller again, Bavuma pushes it towards mid off to get through the over. LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Ashwin starts with a flighted delivery on off and middle, de Kock calmly defends it.
Tossed up on off, de Kock defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! First one of the session. Flighted around off, de Kock looks to drive it on the up but the ball goes off the outside edge through backward point for a boundary.
Floated on off, de Kock blocks it away.
Gives this air, de Kock calmly keeps it out.
A solid front foot defense from de Kock to end the over.
Tossed up on off, Bavuma pushes it to mid on and gets his first run of the session straightaway.

OUT! BOWLED! The ball kept low but that is such an unnecessary shot from de Kock. Jadeja bowls it slower through the air outside off. It pitches on the rough and spins in. The ball keeps low as well. De Kock for some absurd reason goes for a big slog sweep but the ball goes between the bat and pad onto the middle stump. Quinton will not be happy looking at his shot selection once he has a look back. Brilliant start for India! Half the side back in the hut for South Africa.
Floated on off, Muthusamy blocks it with a dead-bat to start his innings.
Tossed up around off, Muthusamy keeps it out.
Loopy ball on the stumps, Senuran calmly defends it.
Flatter now from Jadeja. Muthusamy defends it.
Flighted on off, Bavuma pushes it towards mid off and gets to the other end.
Tossed up on middle and off, Ashwin defends it off the front foot.
Beauty! Flighted around off, Muthusamy looks to drive it on the up but the ball turns away and beats the outside edge of the bat.
Another gem. This one is given more air by Ashwin. It pitches and spins away. Muthusamy tries to defend but gets squared up.
Wow! Ashwin is bowling delicious balls here. Another flighted delivery on off, Senuran tries to defend but has no answer to Ashwin's spin.
Fuller on off, Muthusamy blocks it.
Floated on off, Bavuma keeps it out.
Shorter on the stumps, Temba blocks it off his back foot.
Shorter on middle, Bavuma gets on his back foot and whips it late towards square leg.

FOUR! Up and over! This shot was exceuted well and that is why there will be praise for this shot but had it not come off even Bavuma would have been embarrassed  like de Kock and Elgar. Tossed up on off, Temba sees the mid off is up so he confidently lofts it over the man and fetches himself a boundary.
On the stumps, Bavuma defends it.
Floated on off, Bavuma looks to flick but the ball goes off the inner half of his bat towards square leg for a single.
Around off, Bavuma lunges forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller around off, Bavuma drives it towards cover and takes a run.
Fires this one around off and middle, Muthusamy pushes it back to Ashwin.

Ouch! That would've hurt. Fuller ball on off, Muthusamy goes for the drive and connects well but finds Rohit Sharma in the way at silly point. He is hit just above his heels and looks in pain there, takes some time and is now ready to go.
Fuller ball on off, Muthusamy looks to drive but misses.
Fuller outside off, a loopy ball. Senuran drives it through covers for a couple.
Flatter on off, Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Bavuma defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, Bavuma leaves it alone.
Flighted closer to the off pole, Temba defends it nicely.
Beautifully bowled! Jadeja bowls it slower through the air on off, Bavuma looks to defend but is beaten by the away spin.
Very well fielded. Tossed up on off, Bavuma pushes to the right of cover. Kohli at short cover dives and saves runs for his side.
Flighted on off, Muthusamy blocks it.
Flighted on off, Senuran defends it.
On off, Muthusamy blocks it.
Tossed up around off, Muthusamy looks to defend but the ball spins away and goes past the bat to the keeper.
Fuller on off, Senuran pushes it towards mid off.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Floated on off, Bavuma looks to defend but gets beaten.
Flighted on middle, Bavuma defends it this time.
Darted around the pads, Bavuma glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on off, Muthusamy drives it but it hits Mayank Agarwal on the shin. Thanks to the pads he is wearing that it won't hurt him.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shorter around off, Muthusamy looks to defend but the ball hits him high on the pad.
FOUR! A rare short ball outside off from Ashwin. Bavuma cuts it through backward point. The fielder at short third man dives but gets nothing on it.
Floated around off, Bavuma defends it towards point.
Flighted outside off, Bavuma looks to sweep but misses. The ball hits him on the pads. There is a stiled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On the pads, Bavuma looks to turn it away on the leg side but the ball lobs off his pad fine down the leg side for a couple.
On the stumps, defended by Bavuma.
Shortish length around off, Senuran drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Fuller on off this time, Muthusamy guides it towards point to take a single
Beaty from Jadeja! Jadeja floats this around off. The ball turns away a hint to beat the outside edge.
FOUR! Bavuma looking solid. Jadeja gives it a lot of air around off on a fullish length, Bavuma leans into the drive and drives it through point and it races to the fence. 100 up for the visitors.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller around off, driven straight to the fielder at cover.
Flighted fuller ball around off, Muthusamy comes forward to defend but can't get bat on ball. He is hit on the shoulder and the ball goes to Rahane at slip.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off this time, Senuran leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fuller ball around off, Senuran drives it handsomely through covers to earn his first boundary.
Beaten because of the away turn. Ashwin floats it around off. Senuran comes forward to drive but can't connect.
Edged but doesn't carry. Jadeja flights it around off,  Bavuma goes to defend with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and falls just short of Pujara. The batters take two.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On off and middle, Bavuma defends it out.
Fuller and on middle, Bavuma looks to work it down the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads. No short leg there.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
SIX! A rank hop ball from Jadeja. Bavuma rocks back and hammers it over the fence. Some confusion if the ball has gone over the fence. The umpires check and signal a six.
On the pads, Senuran tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Around off, Senuran defends it out.
Outside off, Muthusamy leaves it alone. The ball turns away from Saha. Rahane at first slip does well to field.
Fuller ball around off, Senuran lunges forward to keep it out.
Fullish length ball, Muthusamy drives it to mid off.
Another full ball around off, Muthusamy keeps it out.
Shami starts with a loose ball on the pads, Bavuma glances it towards backward square leg and gets a couple.

Almost chopped on. Slightly fuller around off, the ball tails back in a bit. Bavuma looks to defend it to the off side with a slant bat but the ball goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Comes around the wicket and hits the deck hard around off, Muthusamy dabs it towards gully.
Full on middle and off, Senuran does well to block it. That length got the cubical here to go ohh and ahh.
Good length ball on top of middle, Muthusamy defends it with authority.
That was a beauty! Fuller ball on off, the ball zips away off the surface. Senuran looks to defend but gets beaten.
Flighted on off, Bavuma defends it back towards the bowler.
Floated outside off, Bavuma pads it away.
Shorter on off, Temba blocks it off the front foot.
Floated outside off, Bavuma looks to defend but gets beaten.
Flighted on off and middle, Temba nudges it towards mid on for one.
Darts one around the pad, Senuran looks to defend but the ball lobs behind square on the leg side. There were shouts of catch it but not sure whether it came off the bat or pad.

FOUR! Educated edge! Full around off, Bavuma looks to defend but it goes off the edge and wide of gully for a boundary. Rahane puts in a dive but cannot get close to it. Vihari gives it a chase but comes second in the race.
Back of a length ball on off and middle, Bavuma looks to fend it off but it goes to the on side off the inner half of his bat and they take a couple.
Fuller on  off, Bavuma drives it nicely but straight to cover.
Fuller on off, Bavuma keeps it out.
On the pads, Temba glances it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off, Muthusamy keeps it out.

SAFE! No glove and the ball is way outside off. Tossed up around off, Bavuma looks to sweep but the ball lobs off towards first slip. Rahane takes it on the up. The Indian players gather and Kohli takes the review. Replay rolls in and first it shows the ball was missing both the bat and glove. Ball Tracker comes up next and it shows that the impact was outside off and the ball was missing off stump by a mile. India lose one of their two reviews.

OUT! Caught! Bavuma's fight comes to an end. Floated delivery around off, Bavuma looks to drive it to the off side. The ball though spins away and kisses the outside edge. It goes to the left of Rahane at first slip. The Indian Test side's vice captain dives on that side and takes an excellent catch.
Flighted on off, Philander pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Philander defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Philander strokes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
On the stumps, Muthusamy blocks it.
Good length ball closer to the off pole, Philander looks to defend but gets an inside edge.
Superb bouncer from Shami! Shami bends his back and bowls a short ball around middle. Vernon looks to fend it off but is hit on the gloves. It lobs in the air but lands in no man's land.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Goes full around off, Philander drives it sweetly through covers. The ball races towards the fence but Umesh Yadav comes after it and stops a run with a dive. Three runs for Philander.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shami strikes. Change of angle has done the trick. The second innings' Shami has arrived. He got a short leg fielder for the left-hander. He bowls a back of a length ball around off, Senuran looks to fend it off of his toes but the ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Rohit Sharma at second slip. Very seldom we get to see an Indian bowler bouncing out a batsman with a short ball on the fourth day Indian surface. Top stuff from Mohammed Shami. India just three wickets away from a win.
Shami welcomes Maharaj with a bouncer o around the body. Maharaj ducks under it.
Outside off, Philader leaves it alone.
SIX! Up and over. Flighted ball on off and middle, Philander gets into the position and hammers it over the bowler's head to get six.
SIX! Back-to-back six. This one is even bigger. Jadeja delivers it in the slot, Philander slogs it over the long on fence. Top shot that one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Around off, nicely blocked by Philander.
Quicker one on the pads, nudged towards square leg for a single.
Good length ball closer off pole, Philander goes to his back foot and punches it towards cover for a single.
WIDE! Bouncer bounces too high. It goes over Maharaj's head to the keeper.
Goes fullish around off, Maharaj pushes it towards cover. Jadeja hares at the ball and underarms it onto the stumps and non stirker's end. Hits the wicket but Philander never left the crease.
Bouncer down the leg side. Maharaj ducks.
Another bouncer! Maharaj does well to evade it.

Beaten! A massive appeal but not out says the umpire. A pacy good length ball pitching on middle and leg, the ball comes back in after pitching. Keshav Maharaj looks to play it on the off side but it takes something and goes to the left of Saha. He takes the ball on the full. A huge appeal follows but the umpire shakes his head.  Virat Kohli thinks about the review. Rohit Sharma though comes from slips and indicates it is too high. Indicating they were thinking of LBW. Virat listens to the advice and does not refer it.
Fuller around off, pushes towards cover for a single.
Around off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Flighted ball on off, Maharaj defends it towards mid off and takes a quick single. Kohli there couldn't gather the ball cleanly.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted ball on middle, Philander defends it out.
On middle, it is kept out.
A quicker one on the middle, Philander defends it out onto the wicket.
Shami is aiming the body as he delivers another bumper. Maharaj ducks under it.
Around off on a good length, Maharaj this time defends it off the front foot.
Bouncer angled into the batter around off. Maharaj sways away from it.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Length ball on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Good length ball angled into the batter, Maharaj tucks it behind square for a single.
Flights this one on middle, it is kept out.
A quicker one on middle, Maharaj goes back and cuts it straight to point.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Pujara is the man who has spilled it. Jadeja bowls this slower through the air and invites Maharaj for a drive. He obliges and goes for the shot. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards slip. Pujara at second slip throws his left hand to catch but the ball doesn't stick to his palms and lobs behind. He makes a valiant effort to catch it in the second attempt to catch but collides with Rahane who is also trying to get to the ball. Both slip and can't hold on. Had he pouched it, this would've been third catch on multiple attempts. Rahane would've gobbled it without much trouble, one can say.
Beaten this time! Jadeja fires this one at 99.8 kmph around off, the ball turns a hint away to beat the outside edge. Saha behind the wicket can't gather it.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Another ball around the off stump line but it wasn't too wide of the off stump. Maharaj leaves it alone.
Short outside off, Philander punches it to cover.
Flighted around off, Vernon keeps it out.
Off spinner around off, Philander defends it onto the ground, away from short leg.
Flighted outside off, Vernon leaves it alone.
Tossed up around off, Philander looks to defend but it comes off the inside edge. No casualty though as the ball hits him on the pad.
Off spinner which is short and around leg, Philander looks to turn it behind square on the leg side but it goes off the thigh pad towards leg gully.
On the stumps, Maharaj defends it.
Short outside off, Maharaj looks to cut but misses.
Short again, Maharaj defends it off the back foot.
Floated outside off, Maharaj leaves it alone.
Floated on off, Keshav pushes it to cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Short ball around off, Philander is cramped for room as he looks to punch. The ball goes to the off side off the inner half of his bat.
FOUR! Uppish but safe. Short and wide outside off, Keshav has a slash at it. It goes off the outside edge wide and over first slip for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Maharaj keeps it out.
Floated outside off, Keshav leaves it alone.

FOUR! Cut away! Short around off, Maharaj cuts it through point. Umesh Yadav gives it a chase and tries to pull it back before the ropes but he fails in doing so. Full marks for the effort though for Umesh!
Tossed up outside off, Maharaj leaves it alone.
Shorter in middle, Philander tucks it to the on side.
Flighted on off, Philander keeps it out.

In the air but safe! Jadeja is furious. Floated on middle and leg, Philander looks to play the inside out shot. He ends up edging it uppishly towards backward point. It goes to the right of Ishant Sharma. He does not go for the catch and Jadeja lets out a huge grunt. Single taken.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. They pick up a single.
Flighted on off, Philander keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Vernon pushes it to mid off.
A quicker one off, Maharaj blocks it out.
Slower through the air on middle, Maharaj comes forward to defend but gets an inside edge. Could've easily lobbed to short leg.
On the the pads, Maharaj flicks it to mid-wicket.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, Philander blocks it out.
Around off, Philander gets behind the line of the ball to block.
Fuller ball, it is kept out.
On the pads this time, nudged onto the pitch on the leg side.
Slightly quicker on around off, Vernon pushes it towards cover.
Jadeja is mixing his pace well here. He this time fires it at 93.3 kmph on the pads. Philander flicks it towards the leg side and takes a run.
Around off, blocked out by coming forward.
Slower through the air around middle, Philander flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a run.
Beaten! A quicker ball around off, Maharaj goes to cut but is beaten.

Almost a wicket for Rohit. One wonders why he doesn't bowl often. Rohit lands it around off and gets it spin sharply. Maharaj looks to defend but is hit on the pads. A stifled appeal follows but nothing from the umpire.
On the pads, nudged towards the leg side for a run.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

Shortish length ball, Maharaj rocks back and punches it off the back foot through the cover-point region. The ball was racing towards the fence but Ishant dives to save a run for the side. They check for the clean stop and it shows it is a clean stop.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle, it is kept out.
On the pads, Philander keeps it out.
On the pads again, Philander nudges it behind square and picks a couple.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shortish length outside off, Philander cuts it through point to get a single.
Flighted fuller ball around off, Philander defends it out.
Outside off, Philander defends it back to the bowler.
Outside off again, Philander keeps it out.
Another ball outside off, Philander goes back and keeps it out. Saha is asking Rohit to bowl on middle stump line. Let's see if he obliges.
He does! Rohit bowls it on middle, Philander though tucks it towards square leg for single.
A full ball around off, driven straight to mid off.
Another fuller ball, Philander looks to drive but gets it through the inner half of the bat.

FOUR! This is full again and in the slot outside off for Philander. He gets to the pitch of the ball and hammers it through the covers to get a boundary. Ashwin doesn't look pleased with his own effort.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Around off, it is kept out by Philander.
Full again, Philander pushes it to mid off with ease.
Slower through the air around off, Maharaj comes forward to defend it out.
A quicker one on middle, Maharaj does well to block it off the back foot.
Jadeja fires it quick on middle again, Maharaj looks to work it around the corner but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards the leg side.
Outside off, Maharaj leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, Maharaj goes for the flick but misses.
Flighted ball on off, Maharaj keeps it out. With that, it is TEA on Day 4.
Bowls one wide outside off, Philander leaves it alone.
On middle, Philander blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Full toss outside off, Philander drives it through covers uppishly. Ashwin dives to his right to stop but can't get hands to it.
On middle, it is kept out.
Another yorker on middle. Philander keeps it out.
Full toss on the pads, pushed through mid on for a single.
Good length ball angled into the leg stump. Maharaj goes for the flick but misses. Saha and Umesh appeals but nothing from the umpire.
Around off on middle, Maharaj stands tall and blocks it out.
Sprays the ball way down the leg side. Maharaj goes for the pull again but misses.
Bouncer this time. KM ducks under it.
Play and a miss! Good length ball in the channel outside off. Maharaj goes for the expansive drive but can't get bat on ball.

FOUR! Hammered! Yadav goes for the bouncer but looked as if there was hardly any energy. It doesn't bounce much and Maharaj hammers it to the mid-wicket fence. The boundary brings back-to-back 50-run stand between the two.
Flighted on the stumps, Philander keeps it out.
On the pads, Philander flicks it to the on side for a single.
Floated on off, Maharaj pushes it towards cover for a single.
Tossed up on the stumps, Vernon keeps it out.
Floated around off, Philander drives it wide of silly point towards cover-point for a couple.
Tossed up on off, Philander defends it off the front foot.
Almost! What a reverse swinging delivery from Umesh. Maharaj looks to push it straight but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length ball around off, Maharaj blocks it out.
Sprays down the leg side! Maharaj goes for the flick but misses.
Another ball down the leg side from Umesh on a good length. Maharaj again goes for the flick but misses. Umesh needs to get his line right.
He does this time as he lands it around off, Maharaj defends it out.
And now he bowls it down the leg side again. His problems from forever. Maharaj again goes for the flick and misses again.
Flighted ball on middle, Philander blocks it onto the pitch on the off side.
A quicker one on off, Philander defends it out.
A quicker one around off, pushed towards point.
On middle, it is kept out.

Fuller ball this time, Philander pushes it back to the bowler. Jadeja looks to deflect it onto the stumps but he fails to do so. The ball goes towards mid off. Kohli there dives and stops the ball but a single taken.

How did that miss the stumps? Just over the stumps. Jadeja gives it a lot of air and bowls it full. Maharaj comes forward to defend but the ball shoots off the surface and goes over the stumps. Saha is hit on the chest as he looks to grab it.

OUT! CAUGHT! The consistent bad ball has actually produced the breakthrough. Once again Umesh bowls it full and down the leg side. Philander looks to flick but the ball takes a slight edge and goes to the left of the keeper. Saha moves swiftly to that side and takes a fine catch. The 56-run stand is broken. Lucky breakthrough for Umesh but he isn't complaining.
Full and just outside off, Rabada leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off and middle, Rabada defends it towards point and shouts a loud no.
Bouncer! Kagiso ducks under it.
FOUR! Overpitched around off, Rabada gets on his front foot and drives it off the meat of his bat through covers for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! The over ends the way it started. India now just a wicket away from wrapping up this game. Fuller outside off, Rabada looks to defend but then decides to leave. Too late though as the ball finds the edge and goes to the man at second slip. Rohit Sharma bends forward and takes a good catch.
Tossed up on off, Maharaj pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! The on-field umpire is spot on! Three reds and South Africa have been bundled out. Shorter pitching on off, Keshav looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him on his back pad. The Indian players go up in a loud and confident appeal. The umpire nods his head and raises his finger. Maharaj takes it upstairs. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows that there was no bat involved and then Ball Tracker shows three reds. The ball was clipping the leg pole. INDIA WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 137 RUNS.
